title: barbecue blue fish or striper
directions: Place fillets on foil.
Put mayonnaise over fillets.
Slice onion and put on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fold foil like a tent.
Place on grill and cook for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Boil together rhubarb, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Take off stove and add pineapple and jello.
Pour into sterile jars and lids.
Seal.

title: fried meat pies
directions: Brown meat and add onions and other seasonings near end of browning. Cut off heat and add sauce and lemon juice. Stir in flour. If mixture seems too dry, some meat stock or a little water may be added.

title: chicken celicia
directions: Bone cooked chicken and cut into bite size.
Mix soup and sour cream- make 2 layers of chicken- divide soup-cream mixture over each layer.
Coarsely crush crackers and toss in melted butter.
Place on top of casserole and sprinkle almonds over cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees in a 9 x 9 or 9 x 11 baking dish.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Combine thawed and drained broccoli and next 4 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Put into a large bowl.
Cook in microwave until cheese melts all the way, then form into balls.

title: orange muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add with flour to the butter mixture.
Fill muffin pans and bake at 400°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix orange juice with brown sugar.
Pour over muffins and remove from pans immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with a fork.
Spray glass baking pan with cooking spray.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown patties in skillet with oil. Drain patties.
Blend remainder of soup with water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until patties are cooked through.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or egg noodles.
Serves 6.

title: ruby red temple
directions: In each of four 6-ounce glasses, spoon 2 teaspoons of cranberry juice concentrate and fill to the rim with ginger ale.
Stir, then drop cherry and orange slice into glass.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Put in blender and mix salad oil, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over vegetables and mix together.
Place in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Keeps well for 2 weeks.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer first four ingredients over crust in order listed.
Make pattern on Cool Whip with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.
Each serving counts as: 1/2 bread, 3/4 fruit, 1/4 milk, 1 fat, 58 optional calories.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Peel shrimp, reserving shells and heads.
Cover and refrigerate shrimp until ready to use.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour and water; pour mixture over butter, then pour fruit in over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add milk and cook over medium heat until it bubbles.
Stir constantly until thick.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Add to white sauce.
Mix and heat through.

title: michigan baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix gently, but well.
Place in bean pot casserole dish or slow cooker.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, 5 to 6 hours.
Cover last hour or heat on low in slow cooker overnight. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: magic lemon meringue(makes one 8-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
medium bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in sweetened condensed
milk, lemon juice and rind.
Turn into shell.
In small
bowl,
beat
egg	whites	with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually
add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Bake 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.	Cool. Chill
before
serving.
Refrigerate
any leftovers.

title: joyce's cinnamon walnuts
directions: Mix egg white with walnuts until well coated.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together in a bowl.
Tumble walnuts in dry ingredients.
Spread nuts out on a cookie sheet (ungreased). Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Pry nuts off sheet and spread on newspaper until cool.
Store in airtight container.
This recipe fills 2 medium size nut dishes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: In a medium saucepan sprayed with no-stick spray, saute the mushrooms and onion in the wine over medium heat until tender. Stir in the broth and transfer mixture to a blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Return mixture to the saucepan and set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together 1/4 cup of the milk and the cornstarch until smooth.
Stir the cornstarch mixture into the mushroom mixture, then stir in the remaining 3/4 cup milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.

title: cinnamon cake swirl
directions: Roll each part of dough into a rectangle 12 x 10-inches. Spread each with half the butter.
Mix sugar, nuts, raisins and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of mixture evenly on each rectangle. Roll up, beginning at wide end.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal well.
Stretch to make even and 12 inches long.
Cut each roll into 12 (1-inch) slices.
Line 10-inch tube pan with foil. Grease and arrange 8 slices of dough with cut sides against outer sides of pan.
Arrange 8 slices with cut sides up on bottom of pan.
Stagger a second layer on top slices in bottom of pan. Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes. Glaze.

title: baked cranberry sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Turn into a 6 cup baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve very warm, straight from the baking dish.
Refrigerate leftovers and serve reheated within a week or so.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry rice in oil until golden brown.
Carefully add liquids and remaining ingredients.
Stir well and cover.
After it comes to boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Don't peak or stir until done.

title: rice pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, mix rice, light cream, milk, sugar and salt.
Cover and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Lightly mix egg yolks with vanilla and slowly add to hot rice, stirring constantly.
Cook a few minutes to thicken.
Empty into bowl.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.
Whip cream and add to cold rice.
May be served with strawberry or other fruit sauce, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: no oil spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl; beat until smooth, using medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake according to cake mix package directions.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: omelet in a bag
directions: Prepare whatever you like in your omelet.
Boil a half pan of water.
Scramble only one egg.
Put egg and all of your ingredients in your Ziploc Baggie.
Hold Ziploc in the pan of boiling water until omelet is firm.
Remove omelet from Baggie. Only use one egg because it wouldn't get done and Baggie will melt.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice and butter; let melt, then mix all of the above.
Mix well; top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until just tender and cool.
Mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, pepper and salt.
Place carrots and soup mixture in large bowl.
Add onions, bell pepper and mushrooms. You may add other vegetables such as celery, zucchini, if desired. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
It's better if left overnight. Will keep 2 weeks if refrigerated.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: yams hawaiian style
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle top with pecans and brown sugar.
Bake in moderate oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain and set aside.

title: rocky-road bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in whole egg and 2 egg yolks. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine the two mixtures and blend thoroughly.

title: blackberry pie filling cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Add blackberry filling. Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Use three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugars and eggs.
Then add zucchini, beat and add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in a greased and floured pan.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch.
Stir in meat, cheese, onions, pepper and seasonings.
Pour in unbaked frozen pie shell at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.
Can be baked and frozen.

title: blackberry cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, gelatin, oil and milk.
Mix until blended.
Add eggs, one at at time beating well after each. Fold in the blackberries, coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased 9 inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done, cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to wire racks.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix with all other ingredients except cheese crackers.
Pour into Pam sprayed Pyrex dish.
Crush very fine enough cheese crackers to cover. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Add sugar to vinegar in bottle and shake until sugar is dissolved.
Add other ingredients and store in bottle in refrigerator with lid on.
Use on lettuce or other salads.

title: guess again cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats, rice cereal, coconut and pecans.
Mix by hand.
Roll in small balls. Press with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: chocolate almond biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, salt and almonds.
In small bowl, combine vanilla and almond extract and egg product.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until well blended.
Dough will be dry.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for butter.
Then take a medium size glass casserole dish and put 1 stick of butter in it and place it in the oven until it melts.
After it has melted, mix in the other ingredients and mix together lightly.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour together.
Add boiling water and salt.
Stir and cook for 6 to 8 minutes.
If too thick, add a little more boiling water.
Remove from heat and add butter or margarine, cream and vanilla.
Blend well and keep warm until served.

title: rice santa fe
directions: Brown rice in 1 tablespoon oil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Turn rice out; add remaining oil and brown beef, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add soup, water, garlic salt and pepper.
Mix well and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain, then rinse under cold water.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Add sauce, cheese, mushrooms and juice.
Stir well.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hello dolly bar cookies
directions: Melt margarine in square baking dish. Pour crumbs over melted margarine, but do not stir. Pour chocolate drops over crumbs, then put a layer of coconut, then layer of chopped pecans. Pour sweetened condensed milk over all, but do not stir. Bake at 350° until it bubbles. Yield: 16 bars.

title: coconut chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place mixture in greased and floured 15 X 10 X 1 inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool and cut into bars.

title: zero fat salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with tightly fitted top.
Shake well before using.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 325° in a tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat on all sides in hot shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet or kettle and simmer slowly 2
or 3 hours, until meat is tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Thicken gravy with flour for serving.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bring sugar and pineapple to a boil and cool.
Mix cake as directed on box and stir in pineapple mixture.
Bake as directed on box.
Let cake cool completely.
Mix pudding as directed on box and pour over cooled cake.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread with whipped topping and garnish with coconut, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: goulash
directions: Boil water in a 32 ounce Dutch oven. Add seashell macaroni; add elbow macaroni.
Cook on medium-high until macaroni is tender. Drain; leave covered.
Brown hamburger.
Season to taste (chopped onion with hamburger).
Drain hamburger; add to drained macaroni. Add tomato juice; simmer until juice thickens.

title: zucchini squash *
directions: Grease and dot a 10-inch dish with margarine.
Slice zucchini in 1/2-inch slices and cover bottom of dish.
Cover with onion rings and pepper rings.
Repeat until all of zucchini, pepper and onion has been used.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add cheese and bread crumbs and bake for 5 minutes more.
Serves 5.

title: peaches a la hailey
directions: Place 8 peach halves on a baking sheet.
Mix the brown sugar, butter and the cinnamon together then evenly divide it between the 8 peaches sprinkling in the center of each one.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Before serving, put a scoop of vanilla ice cream in the center of each peach.

title: meatballs in chili sauce
directions: Soak tortillas in milk in a large bowl for 15 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except taco sauce and broth.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Heat taco sauce and broth to boiling in a 10-inch skillet.
Reduce heat.
Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen meatballs.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until done (still firm).
Add peppers and onions.

title: three bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock-pot.
Cook all day on low.

title: lite pie
directions: Mix 1/2 jello with yogurt and cool whip.
Pour into crust and sprinkle with remaining jello.
Chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Boil beef stew meat 3 to 4 hours or until very tender.
Add butter while boiling.
After meat is tender and falling apart add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are soft.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: saucy butter rolls
directions: Bring milk, sugar and margarine to boil.
Roll each biscuit out flat.
Put 1 pat of margarine and 1 teaspoon sugar in center. Pinch together.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and salt.
Add yeast and milk.
Blend.
Add flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, roll in a circle; spread with butter.
Slice into pie wedges.
Roll each slice from outer edge toward center.
Let rise.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and lay flat to cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until blended. Combine food coloring and cocoa, forming a paste.
Add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Blend in vanilla. Sift flour and salt together.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Combine soda and vinegar to make a foamy liquid. Fold liquid carefully into cake batter by hand.
Do not use electric mixer. Pour batter into two greased and lightly floured 9-inch cake layer pans or a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 24 minutes if using two 9-inch cake layer pans or for 65 minutes if using a 10-inch tube pan.
Cool completely before icing.

title: grandma emma's sugar cookies(freda's grandmother)
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and milk together.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix to make soft dough.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Cut out cookie shapes and bake at 425° on greased cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 150 cookies.

title: cheese balls
directions: Beat all ingredients except pecans until fluffy.
Chill and shape.
Roll in pecans.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients and cook over low heat until bubbly.
Cool completely, then add flour, sugar, baking soda and vanilla.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely, then add peanut butter and oil. Mix and spread over cake.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal. Cover.
Let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture; mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes. Do not remove cake from pan.

title: shrimp in batter
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg; add milk. Add to dry ingredients; beat smooth.
Dip shrimp singly in batter. Fry in shallow oil heated to 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with sauce.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Cut in butter. Add eggs, bananas, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Beat until blended. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 minutes. Remove from pan immediately. Dough will be sticky when mixed. The cookies do not run or spread.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: aunt lydia's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by small teaspoon and press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar and a little cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
They will look light when done.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Make instant pudding according to directions, except use 3 cups instead of 4.
When thickened, add Cool Whip.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with 1 layer of graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix over crackers.
Pour remaining 1/2 of pudding over second layer of crackers.
Cover with third layer of crackers.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and coconut in saucepan and cook
minutes;
stirring
constantly.
Add
nuts
and coconut and beat
until
mixture
is of spreading consistency. Yield: Enough icing for a 2-layer cake.

title: grandma rice
directions: Put everything in a pan and bring to a boil.
Dump into a baking dish and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
If too dry, add a bit of water.

title: orange julius(serving size: 3)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend 20 to 30 seconds.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: buffalo-chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
You can half this recipe.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Melt in double boiler pan the margarine, canned milk and caramels; stir until well blended.
Mix in the Rice Krispies and walnuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on waxed paper and let cool.

title: no-bake chocolate peanut butter squares(candy)
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Pat firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in pan over low heat.
Pour over mixture.
Let set; cut into squares.

title: ham and cheese bake
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves six.

title: carrot (kugel) casserole
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; put aside.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add egg yolks and grated carrots; blend well.
Add dry ingredients, water and lemon juice.
Fold in egg whites.
Place in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven western eggs
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs and then beat in remaining ingredients.
Bake until set at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: layered strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press evenly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine next 9 ingredients in container of electric blender; process 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and leave in oven 1 hour.
Set aside to cool.
Arrange strawberries on top of pie. Combine cornstarch and orange juice in saucepan, stirring well. Cook over low heat 1 minute or until thickened and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour glaze over strawberries; chill.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: pasta and broccoli(with honey-dijon dressing)
directions: Cook shell macaroni according to package directions; drain. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In large bowl, toss cooled shell macaroni with oil.
Add broccoli, carrot and onion; mix well.
Cover and chill, stirring occasionally.
Serve salad on lettuce; spoon dressing over top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine above into mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baby cheesecakes
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in remaining ingredients.
Place a vanilla wafer in the small size muffin tins lined with small baking paper cuts.
Fill close to top of papers with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
These will sink as they cool.
Top each with a spoon full of cherry pie filling. Refrigerate.
Makes 3 dozen.
(Can be topped with other flavor filling.)

title: pork chop parmesan
directions: Brown chops in large skillet.
Remove from pan.
Stir rice, water and 1 cup of sauce in skillet.
Add chops.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and simmer until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line
a 9 x 13-inch pan
with
whole
graham
crackers, bottom and sides.	Mix vanilla pudding
and
cups
of milk. Blend in Cool Whip.	Spread this
over graham crackers and top with another layer of graham crackers.

title: herbed baby potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole, toss potatoes in oil to coat each piece.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley, for garnish.
Toss to coat evenly.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with parsley.

title: apple oat-bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the oat bran, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Stir to mix well.
Add the brown sugar and stir to mix well.
Use the back of a wooden spoon to press out any lumps in the brown sugar.
Put the yogurt, apple juice, egg and oil in a small bowl and stir to mix well.
Add the yogurt mixture to the oat-bran mixture and stir to mix well. Fold in the apple and if desired, the nut or dried fruit.
Coat the bottoms only of muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray and fill 3/4 full with batter.
Bake for about 16 minutes or just until a wooden toothpick inserted into the center of the muffin comes out clean.
Remove the muffin tin from the oven and allow it to sit for 5 minutes before removing the muffins.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Refrigerate or freeze any leftovers not eaten within 24 hours.

title: chex mix
directions: Toss all cereals and pretzels together in large roasting pan. Melt butter and stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire.
Add to cereal and mix until coated.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: french dressing
directions: Heat to mix well and until lumps disappear.

title: jello bundt cake
directions: You also need 1 Bundt pan.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: ann's crunchy cheese dip
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
In a small bowl, combine pineapple, cream cheese, water chestnuts, chives, salt, pepper and pecans.
Stir in juice and mix well. Chill for 2 hours.
Garnish with parsley and serve with assorted crackers.

title: pistachio frosting
directions: Mix pistachio pudding mix together with milk; cream margarine and shortening together with powdered sugar.
Add creamed mixture to pudding mix, blending well.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Simmer 4 hours and remove spices.
A wonderful Christmas beverage.

title: sausage showoffs
directions: Mix biscuit mix according to package directions.
Roll on floured surface into rectangle.
Crumble uncooked sausage to cover rectangle.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in 1/4-inch wheels (or less).
Bake on cookie sheet with sides to prevent grease from dripping.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Combine ingredients until crumb mixture forms.
Press in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Sprinkle 3 cups miniature marshmallows on top and return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows just begin to puff.
Cool.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Mix cheese and sausage and put in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs in a bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in the shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and oil together.
Add zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured angel food pan, Bundt pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until done through (about 40 to 45 minutes). Peel skin off potatoes.
Dice potatoes.
Add sour cream, diced onions and cream of potato soup.
Mix well.
Melt butter.
Add crushed Ritz crackers. Cover cracker mixture on top of casserole. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: smoke egg dip
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except radish; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Chill 1 hour; beat until fluffy.
Garnish with radish slices.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Next brown beef.
Add beans to meat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add to salad mixture. Garnish with tomatoes, avocado and Doritos around edge of bowl. Serve pronto.

title: watergate salad
directions: Toss all ingredients with the mayonnaise.
Add croutons before serving.
This is delicious served with ham!

title: corn fritters
directions: Grind corn and salt.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add flour and milk. Add corn and mix well.
Fry in hot oil by dropping into skillet by spoon.

title: holiday hot toddy
directions: Use heavy glass tumbler.
Fill half full with Jack Daniels whiskey.
Add sugar.
Squeeze lemon and drop into glass.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Fill glass with boiling water.

title: chicken soup with matzoh balls
directions: Follow recipe on package.

title: beef 'n potato bake(quick, easy and good!)
directions: In a shallow, 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and black pepper.
Firmly press mixture across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to boil.
Add peanut butter and Special K.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place Hershey bars on top.
When melted, spread.
Cut while warm.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper and cayenne in shallow dish.
Dip chicken first into buttermilk, then into flour mix to coat completely.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add onion and green pepper.
Cook until wilted.
Add meat and, using edge of a heavy kitchen spoon, stir and chop meat to break up any lumps.
Sprinkle meat with garlic, chili powder, cumin and oregano.
Stir to blend.
Add bay leaf, pepper, tomatoes, vinegar and crushed hot pepper.
Bring to boil and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in oleo for 10 minutes.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
Stir into first mixture.

title: nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into tiny balls and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
Roll in sugar again about 1/2 hour later.

title: crab bagel spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium size bowl.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Place cooled, cooked macaroni, cucumber slices and tomato cubes in large bowl.
Add Italian dressing and toss until well coated. Can serve chilled or room temperature.
Other vegetables such as peppers or carrots can be added.

title: shredded barbecued beef
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown roast on all sides in 1 tablespoon of oil.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix and simmer 30 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate caramel bars(microwave)
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine chocolate chips and Crisco in a large bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir vigorously. Make sure all chips are melted.
Pour cereal into melted chip mixture.
Stir until thoroughly coated.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; gradually add powdered sugar, creaming well.
Add egg and flavorings; beat until fluffy.
Stir in pecans; drop small spoonfuls (or shape into small balls or crescents) on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until creamy tan color.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 6 1/2 to 7 dozen.

title: garbanzo curry
directions: Heat oil in a 5 to 6 quart pan over medium heat. Add yellow onion, celery, bell pepper, and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft but not browned (about 7 minutes). Meanwhile, cut unpeeled potatoes into one inch chunks. To pan, add potatoes, bouillon cubes, water, garbanzos, tomato paste, curry powder, and red pepper; mix well. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to medium; cover and cook until potatoes are tender when pierced (30 to 40 minutes). Spoon rice in a ring on a warm rimmed platter; mound garbanzo mixture in center. Sprinkle with green onions.

title: hot dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs for 2 minutes on top of stove.
Place hot dogs on buns.
Top with favorite toppings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, drain.
In a casserole dish, mix ground beef, cream of chicken soup and onion, spread across the entire bottom of dish and pack flat.
Layer cheese over meat mixture, then tater tots.	Bake until the tater tots are golden brown and cheese is visibly melted, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs, beating well.
Stir in bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift in all dry ingredients. Stir to mix.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into cubes.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Line bottom of casserole dish with cooked rice.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.

title: sausage and mostaccioli bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add sauce, noodles and Parmesan cheese. Mix well.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 4 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella.
Microwave 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: red cheese enchiladas
directions: Boil red dry chiles for 2 minutes.
In blender combine your chiles, salt and garlic with 1 1/2 cups water.
Blend for 5 minutes.
Deep fry tortillas in oil.
Dip into red chile sauce.

title: pumpkin pie bars
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside 1 cup cake mix. In small bowl, lightly beat 1 egg.
In large bowl, stir together remaining cake mix, melted butter and beaten egg.
Press into prepared pan.
In large mixing bowl, lightly beat remaining 3 eggs; stir in pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, evaporated milk and cinnamon.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
To the reserved cake mix, add the remaining 1/2 cup sugar, walnuts and softened butter; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mix.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and saute chopped onion.
Drain excess grease.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Add canned vegetables and simmer 45 minutes.

title: salmon macaroni salad
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove bones and skin.
Combine salmon, peas and macaroni.
Chill.
Season to taste, add salad dressing.
Toss slightly.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with slices of hard-boiled egg.

title: paula's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Mash squash.
Add soup, sour cream, carrot, salt and pepper.

title: california medley
directions: Microwave veggies according to package directions.
Drain well when cooked.
In a medium saucepan, melt cheese and milk until completely melted.
Pour over veggies; mix well.
In a skillet melt butter and brown crushed crackers.
Top veggies with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is browned and bubbly.

title: wine cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except small mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough mixture in little balls, then roll balls in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
(The balls should be the size of small meatballs.)

title: date balls
directions: Heat over medium heat, margarine, dates and brown sugar until dates have melted.
Combine in pecans, coconut, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut and place on wax paper.

title: frozen strawberries
directions: Makes 5 1/2 quarts or 40 (4 ounce) servings.
Ice ring or floating sherbet is nice on top.

title: jam bars
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut in 1 1/2 cups shortening or butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of the crumbly mixture on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 15 x 10 x 1-inch ungreased baking pan.
Spread with 2 cups of any kind of jam.
The jam will spread easier if you beat it with a fork before spreading.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° until brown and firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots slightly, allowing to boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain at once.
Place cooked carrots, raw onions and peppers in layers. Cover with marinade.
Prepare at least 12 hours in advance.
Will keep in covered container in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: sweet and hot tartar sauce
directions: After chopping, drain all vegetables on paper towels to avoid

title: banana nut loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl combine ingredients in the order they are listed.
Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
Makes 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaves.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut up all vegetables and boil until soft.
Cook rice separate, then add to mixed vegetables.

title: sweet potato cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl cream together butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and sweet potatoes. Mix well.
Gradually stir in sifted ingredients.
Fold in nuts. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: 5-minute blender pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch pie pan.
Spread top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crock pot minestrone soup
directions: Use 6-quart kettle.
Cook hamburger, garlic, onion and celery in oil.
Stir in tomato paste and next seven ingredients.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer slowly one hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Tastes better the longer it cooks.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars and oil.
Add 2 well-beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add cream of tartar, flour, soda and salt.
Then add Rice Krispies, oat flakes and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Get a large platter.
Arrange the first 7 ingredients one on top of each other on platter.
Start with jalapeno bean dip and end with shredded cheese.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: garden vegetable stir-fry
directions: Blend broth, soy sauce and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat oil in wok.
Stir-fry meat, ginger root and garlic, until mostly cooked. Add vegies and stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add nuts; stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Add soup mixture.
Cook until bubbly.
Cover and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve on rice or Chinese noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Add 2 quarts 7-Up and 1 small jar maraschino cherries.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Pour ground beef into casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Spread corn over the soup and sprinkle with cheese.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Brown potatoes on broil if desired.

title: quick beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Line casserole dish with beef.
Place sliced potatoes on top of beef.
Pour cream of chicken soup (undiluted) on top of potatoes.
Put pats of margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Add to broccoli and stir.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in pan.
Add 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm herb crumb mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple stuffed pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt over both sides of pork chops.
Saute apple and onion in butter in a medium saucepan until soft.
Stir in bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon of water.
Stuff into pockets of chops. Fasten with toothpicks.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients; fry in hot skillet, dropping by spoonfuls in hot grease, turning when brown.

title: grilled cheese bread
directions: Heat grill.
With serrated knife, slice bread lengthwise in half, horizontally.

title: spicy tomato mini-loaves
directions: Combine
corn
flakes,	1/2 cup tomato soup, onion, egg and horseradish.
Mix
in
ground beef.
Portion meat mixture into
6 parts.
Shape into individual loaves or ovals.
Place on foil-lined	baking	sheet
or pan.	Mix together remaining soup, brown sugar and mustard.
Spread evenly over meat.	Bake in
oven	about
minutes or until meat is cooked. Yields 6 servings.

title: caldillo (mexican stew)
directions: Saute beef and onions in bacon fat.
Add all other ingredients, except potatoes.
Simmer until beef is tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add potatoes during last 30 minutes.
(Freezes well.)

title: good punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Add rest of ingredients. Bring back to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Place in qt. containers and freeze.
To serve:
In large punch bowl add 1 qt. punch mixture and 1 qt. water.
Float orange slices and strawberries. Add ice ring.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Broil cabbage until soft.
Roll sausage into cabbage leaves. Place in baking pan.
Put sliced onions on top.
Mix tomato juice and sauce.
Pour over rolled cabbage leaves.
Lay bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Any extra cabbage leaves are placed on bottom and top of pan.

title: beef and rice
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Add soups and rice to ground beef.
Mix together.
Pour into a large baking dish. Bake 1 hour in oven at 300°.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large Ziploc bag, combine all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until all potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes onto shallow cookie sheet.
Bake, turning occasionally, 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup, soy sauce and pepper, stir until smooth.
Mix in beans and 1 1/2 cans onions.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more. Yields 20 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: viennese cocoa
directions: In saucepan, combine cocoa, sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in boiling water.
Pour in milk, stirring.
Over medium-low heat, heat cocoa until tiny bubbles form.
Remove from heat.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat until foamy before serving.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix well and congeal.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve with carrot sticks, cauliflower, celery, broccoli and or chips.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Put in heavy
pan
and melt over low heat the butter or oleo, water and
Karo.
When
hot, add sugar.
Cook to 310° on candy thermometer.
Be
careful.	At
this heat it will scorch easily. Pour
out on well buttered cookie sheet.
When partly cool, sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
When soft, spread with knife. Refrigerate until cool.
Crack with knife.

title: potato and pork chops
directions: Slice potatoes and layer in dish.
Layer sliced sweet pepper. Salt as layer in casserole.
Put cans of mushroom soup over mixture (clean can with water).
Slice onion and layer.
Roll pork chops in flour and put on top.
Put remaining soup on top.
Bake until brown.

title: "microwave banana bread"
directions: Grease small glass Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar, 1/4 cup pecans and cinnamon.
Combine remaining dry ingredients in bowl.
Add margarine, milk, egg and bananas; mix well.
Fold in remaining 1/4 cup pecans.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Microwave on Medium for 9 minutes.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until bread tests done.
Let stand for several minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
12 slices.

title: hot spiced lemon-appleade
directions: Place water, spices and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high flame; reduce flame.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add juices. Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cube the cheese.
Combine the cheese and the Rotella in a double boiler.
Melt cheese.
This recipe works well in the microwave or crock pot also.

title: crumb slices
directions: Cream together cake mix and butter or margarine and put 2/3 cup aside for topping.
Add cinnamon and brown sugar to reserved topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with fresh blueberries, then beat sour cream and egg together.
Pour over fruit.
Then top with the reserved topping. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and beans
directions: In saucepan, fry garlic gently in the oil until golden brown. Add tomato sauce and water; cook for 10 minutes.
Add beans; stir gently.
Continue to cook on simmer.
Cook pasta al dente; drain and add to bean mixture.
Stir gently.
If it gets too thick, add a little more water.
Add parsley.
Serve immediately, or else pasta will absorb all liquid.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown onions in cooker.
Put in all other ingredients.
Cover with water; add salt.
Cook until done, 40 minutes.
Stir together the flour and 1/4 cup of water; add milk.
Pour into soup.
Cook 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in 10-inch pie plate.
Mix sugar, cheese and flour and cover pineapple.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers to cover mixture.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes and mash.
Add remainder of ingredients, except marshmallows.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Cook butter, molasses and brown sugar for 5 minutes until thick.
Put in bottom of 9x13 dish.
Slice bread (1 1/2 inch slices) and place on top of sauce.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix 3 Tbsp. sugar and 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon; sprinkle over bread. Melt 1/4 cup butter and drizzle over top.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.
Serves
6-8 people.
(Recipe can easily be doubled or halved.)
Good for breakfast or brunch.

title: sherried beef and spinach
directions: Remove and discard fat from meat.
Cut meat across the grain into thin slices.
Cut each slice in half.
Flatten meat slightly by pressing with fingers.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Add peanut butter, egg, milk and vanilla.
Gradually blend in the dry ingredients and mix well. Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down to secure.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage leaves, trimming away all tough parts.
Place leaves to tenderize.
Mix all ingredients.
When leaves are tender, put a large spoon of the meat-rice mixture in each leaf. A toothpick may be used to help hold the cabbage around the meat. Put rolls in a pan with cover.
Add the can of V-8 juice and cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of bell peppers; remove seeds and membranes. Precook peppers in boiling salted water about 5 minutes.
Drain. Sprinkle insides of peppers generously with salt.
Cook 1 lb. ground beef and 1/3 cup chopped onion (season with salt and pepper.) Prepare Spanish rice.
Stir in 4 oz. sharp cheese. Stuff peppers. Stand upright in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.	Baked uncovered (in water) at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Top with tomato sauce.

title: crowd pleasing potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes w/bay leaf until 3/4 done;
cool, peel and coarsely great.
Heat butter, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, onions and 1 1/2 c. cheese.
Gently stir sauce into 11x7x2 inch casserole.
Bake in 350° gas oven for 30 mins.
Combine remaining (1/2 c.) cheese & crushed corn flakes; sprinkle over casserole and bake 10 to 15 additional mins.

title: oz's salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello together.
Add other fruits. Fold in Cool Whip.
Let stand a few hours in refrigerator for better flavor.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend for 7 minutes. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Top with cinnamon after baking.

title: amy henson's black bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 4 hours or overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Cover the beans with water and simmer 2 to 3 hours
(add more water as needed).

title: chicken with artichokes and peas
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken strips with flour mixture.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot olive oil, cook chicken until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add broth, wine, artichokes and Prosciutto; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peas; cook 5 minutes more or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serves 6.

title: jay's s.o.s.
directions: Fry onion and hamburger in a large frying pan.
When done, push hamburger to one side of pan.
Melt the remaining butter in frying pan.
Add and mix the flour.
Slowly add the milk and half and half.
When sauce starts to thicken, mix the hamburger with the sauce.
Sauce should be nice and thick.
Add salt to taste. Serve over toast.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Chop carrots, celery and garlic.
Bring to a boil with 2 cups water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes and paste, along with 4 cups water and kidney beans. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add elbow macaroni.
Cook until tender. Serve with grated cheese.

title: tomato fritters(south african recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add to it 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs.
Mix.
Drop from spoon on hot greased griddle or large frying pan.
Let cook halfway; turn and brown other side.
Use as any pancake with butter, syrup or gravy.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine broccoli, eggs, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and soup. Place in greased baking dish.
Mix crushed Hi Ho's with butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato slices
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Pour oil into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish and place in the oven until hot, about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes to oiled dish and bake for 20 minutes, turning after 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.
After 20 minutes, remove from the oven and coat with the brown sugar mixture.

Return to the oven and roast for another 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Stir potatoes as necessary to allow them to brown evenly. Remove the potatoes and place on paper towels to drain, then transfer to a serving dish.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake(resembles brownies)
directions: Sift together in a large bowl cake flour and sugar.
Bring to boil oleo, cocoa, Crisco and cold water.
Then pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Mix buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add and mix well.
Pour in well-greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook mostaccioli as directed on box.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix sauces, seasonings and 2 cups of cheese in with meat and add to pasta.
Mix well.
Put into 13x9 pan and sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for approximately 35 minutes.
Serves:

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, water and vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, cocoa, salt and soda; gradually add to creamed mixture and beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes before removing.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: texas chile
directions: Brown chuck, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Place ingredients in saucepan on low heat.
Add tomato sauce and whole tomatoes.
Cook for 2 hours on low heat.
Add pimentos and kidney beans.
Cook another hour. Serve over rice.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into preheated wok.
Boil on high.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook 3 minutes, uncovered, stirring constantly.
Add cornstarch.
When thickened, add meat (pork, chicken, shrimp, etc.) and pineapple.
Serve over white rice.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler, then add sugar and salt; mix well.
When sugar is dissolved, slowly add can of milk; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and cool.
Refrigerate in quart jar.
Heat amount needed to serve.

title: potato salad with hard-boiled eggs
directions: Boil potatoes in a large pot of salted water until done, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Test for doneness with a fork. Drain into a colander and let cool.
Peel skin and cut potatoes into cubes.
Place potatoes in a large mixing bowl and add chopped eggs and onion and remaining ingredients.
Mix with a large spoon and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: smothered cabbage
directions: Salt, pepper, garlic and onion powder meat to taste.
Heat oil in a large pot.
Brown short ribs and add onions.
Put clean cabbage leaves on top.
Continue until all cabbage is cooked. Stir to bring meat up and cabbage on bottom.
Watch to make sure there is at least half a pot of water.
Stir now and then.
Cook until leaves are tender.
Serve over cooked rice.
Enjoy.

title: poor man's dinner
directions: Place cheese between slices of bread and add mayonnaise.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook
rice.
Cook broccoli according to instructions on box. Add
butter and cheese; let melt.
Pour over cooked rice and mix thoroughly.

title: cold rice salad
directions: After cooked, refrigerate Rice-A-Roni until cool.
When cool, mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: cranberry pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin cups with paper liners or grease muffin cups well.
In a bowl, sift together flour, soda, baking powder, spices and salt.
In a large bowl, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in pumpkin.
Add flour mixture, stirring until just blended. Fold in cranberries.
Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling to top of cup.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes for tea cake size, 20 to 25 minutes for regular size muffins.
Makes 26 tea size or 18 regular size.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Place cheeses in small mixing bowl.
Let stand to room temperature until soft.
At low speed, beat in onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy; scraping bowl frequently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add oil and beaten egg.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to mixture. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: summer squash souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread crumbs) together; pour into greased casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Fry in a skillet with a small amount of oil.
Brown on both sides.
May be served with butter or honey.

title: melon mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill.
When slightlyt thickened, fold in melon balls.
Turn into mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; cool, rinse and drain.
Steam vegetables.
Mix pasta and vegetables with dressing and serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, corn meal and diced onion.
Add water until doughy. Drop by large spoonful into hot grease.
Brown on both sides.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and butter; beat.
Add apricot nectar and coconut.
Pour into partly baked pie shells.
Bake at 450° until starts to brown.
Reduce heat to 350° until done, about 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bubble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add walnuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Add milk and stir.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Spoon fruit over top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
May serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix well with ham.
Stir mixture into baked beans.
Put into 2-quart casserole; top with sliced tomatoes.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: happy marriage recipe
directions: Keeps best if not allowed to stew or freeze.
Lasts a lifetime.
Serves 2.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple with Jell-O to the boiling point just until the Jell-O is dissolved; let cool.
Mix softened cream cheese and Cool Whip; gradually add pineapple-Jell-O mixture until well blended. Chill several hours or may be frozen.

title: family peach cobbler
directions: Prepare peaches and mix
with sugar.
Set oven at 350°. Put margarine in a very, deep baking dish or pan.
Set in oven to melt.
Stir up a batter
of
sugar, flour (if you use plain flour, use pinch of salt
and
teaspoons baking powder) and milk. Pour this over melted
margarine
but do not stir.	Put sugared peaches on top.
Do not
stir.
Bake
in 350° oven for 3/4 of an hour.
The batter will
rise
to the top and will be crisp and brown.

title: orange candied sweet potatoes
directions: Pour all but 1/4 cup of juice from potatoes and put into casserole dish.
Combine orange juice and corn syrup and blend well.
Dot with butter or oleo, then pour fluids over sweet potatoes.
Simmer, basting frequently, for 15 minutes.

title: fruit juice frappe
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix about 2 minutes or until ice is finely chopped.
Serve in chilled wine glasses. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Prepare spinach as directed on package.
(You can use fresh spinach, if desired, steam until tender first.)
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and salt lightly.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves well with green salad, fresh fruit, hard bread and white wine.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water and let stand 5 minutes. Dissolve salt in 2 cups warm water.
Put 5 cups of flour in large bowl add wet ingredients and mix well.
Add enough remaining flour to make a workable dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead for 10 minutes, until dough is smooth and elastic and has a satiny sheen.
Place in greased bowl and turn to grease top. Cover; place bowl in warm, draft-free place; let rise until doubled in bulk (approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Turn dough out onto board and knead for 5 minutes more.
Divide dough into two pieces and round each piece into a ball.
Return to greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled (approximately 45 to 60 minutes). Separate pieces of dough.
Roll each ball into an oblong shape using both hands and shape into Italian style loaves.
Sprinkle baking sheet or stone with cornmeal.

Place loaves on baking surface and let rise until doubled (approximately 30 minutes). Make one long slash, about 1 inch deep nearly the entire length. Place loaves in oven which has been heated to 375°.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Brush tops of loaves with egg white wash and sprinkle with seed.
Continue baking another 10 to 20 minutes, until golden brown and bread sounds hollow when tapped.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg with onion.
Drain off any fat.
Season with salt and some pepper.
Bring 3 to 4 quarts water to boil in a large pan with salt.
Add macaroni and boil, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.

title: cold water chocolate cake
directions: Put everything into a bowl and whisk until smooth.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Heat sugar and margarine.
Let cool.
Add eggs, coconut, raisins, pecans and vinegar.
Put in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and cook for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Combine rest of the ingredients. Use as sloppy joe on a bun.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat raw hamburger in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onions.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Put cream of mushroom soup on top of the Tater Tots.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: sugar free cake
directions: Cook raisins, apple and water until water evaporates.
In a large bowl, combine Egg Beaters, sweetener, oil, vanilla and applesauce.
Add nuts to raisins; stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well with a large spoon.
Stir in raisin-nut-apple mixture.
Spray a round or square 10-inch cake pan with vegetable oil spray.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix; set aside.
In a glass oblong dish, start layering with refried beans.
Add taco mix mixture.
Next add chopped olives, onions and tomatoes.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Pour some salsa on top of cheese.
Serve with nachos.
Double for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Thaw frozen potatoes and drain. Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of cheese, all of the sour cream, pepper and 1/2 of onions. Bake in a medium size casserole dish at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Remove cover and top with remaining onions and cheese. Bake for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: warmer kartoffelsalat(hot potato salad)
directions: Boil potatoes; refrigerate 6 hours.
Peel and slice.
Chop bacon and onion and saute until bacon is crisp and onion is transparent.
Add cornstarch, mixed with water, to bacon grease, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and stir for several minutes.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until hot.

title: cheese 'n wiener bake
directions: Saute green pepper and onions in margarine.
Stir in beans, wieners and barbeque sauce.
Pour into 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese; continue baking until cheese has melted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Cook and stir onions and mushrooms until onions are tender; remove vegetables.

title: margarita pie
directions: Mix and put in pie tin: pretzels, sugar and butter.
Mix ice cream in mixer and fill crust and freeze.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: In a metal loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) over very low heat, melt butter.
Set aside off heat.
On a large piece of waxed paper, stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Thoroughly stir in sugar, oats and nuts.
Into large bowl, put thinly sliced bananas.
Beat bananas until they are smooth.
Add egg and beat; add melted butter (from the loaf pan).
Dump in flour mixture with spatula.
Stir just until no white particles of flour show.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked icing
directions: Combine sugar, egg white, cream of tartar and boiling water in a bowl. Mix thoroughly until icing stands in peaks (7-10 minutes). Add vanilla. Make sure cake is completely cool before icing.

title: yam pie
directions: Cook
potatoes
and
mash.
Mix with other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until done.

title: red, white and blue dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and extracts until fluffy. Fold in the whipped cream. Spoon a third of the mixture into a 4-quart bowl. Reserve 19 strawberry halves and 1/2 cup blueberries for garnish. Layer half of the remaining strawberries and blueberries over cream mixture. Top with another third of the cream mixture and the remaining berries. Spread remaining cream mixture over top. Use the reserved strawberries and blueberries to make a flag on top. Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 18 servings.

title: fiesta corn bake
directions: Stir together dip, flour and sugar. Add corn. Spoon into 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with broken corn chips or cheese flavored crackers. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Serves 4.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Heat margarine and sugar in saucepan until melted.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Dust top with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: jarred's favorite brown rice and pork chops
directions: Brown rice in margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour in soup.
Place chops on top. Bake 1 hour, covered, at 375°.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Split spareribs lengthwise.
Marinate in soy sauce overnight. Drain.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, then onion.
Cover with pineapple and bake in covered casserole pan at 400° for 1 1/4 hours, until tender.
Separate each rib for finger eating.

title: apple pie
directions: Line 10-inch pie pan with plain pastry.
Peel, core and slice about 1 1/2 pounds of apples.
This should make 1 quart of apple slices.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon.
Cover bottom of crust with thin layer of sugar mixture.
Fill crust with apple slices and pour rest of sugar mixture over apples.
Dot with butter.
(If apples are not tart, sprinkle juice of half a lemon over pie before adding top crust.)
Adjust top crust and prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed potatoes
directions: Cube Velveeta cheese and melt in microwave.
Add picante sauce and mix.
Add this mixture to ground meat and spoon into baked potatoes.
If in a hurry, microwave potatoes and stuff with mixture.
Easy and fast!
Delicious too!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with the bread slices, buttered side up.
Spread the cooked sausage over top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread over the cheese.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and chop.
Cook rice with seasoning packet.
Combine all ingredients gently.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with crushed corn flakes before baking.
This is a low-fat dish.

title: pineapple-nut-cherry cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add well beaten eggs and mix well.
Add drained, crushed pineapple, cherries and flavoring. Mix nuts in, then add flour-soda mixture a little at a time until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for about 12 minutes at 350°.
Store in airtight container.
This is a moist cookie.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Combine margarine, vanilla, salt and sugar replacement in mixing bowl or food processor; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Press into ungreased 15 x 10-inch (39 x 25 cm) pan.
Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; score into 2 x 1-inch (5 x 2.5 cm) pieces and cool completely.
Break into candy pieces.
Yield: 60 pieces.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt to hard boil (about 250°) consistency.
Put marshmallow cream in mixing bowl.
Pour syrup mixture in, stirring until forms a stiff peak.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and spoon on wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: roast(slow cooker)
directions: Brown roast. In crock-pot, put the roast in, then pour over it the tomato soup, thyme and bay leaves. Add small potatoes, carrots and onions. Cook 8 hours. Do not add water. So good.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar, mustard and salad oil together.
Pour liquid over carrots, onions and pepper and let stand overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; saut onion and celery until tender.
In large mixing bowl, combine rice, celery, and onion with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 qt casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fix jello according to directions on box.
Set in refrigerator until almost set up.
Then add other ingredients and put back in refrigerator until gelled, stirring several times.
Just before serving, stir in 1 container of the small size Cool Whip.

title: charlie's drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and oil.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Refrigerate until firm enough to form into balls.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar.
Form into a ball.
Roll again in powdered sugar. Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream butter and honey; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Turn in a buttered, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll balls in chopped pecans (2 to 3 cups depending on amount of nuts sticking to balls).
Refrigerate until firm.

title: ladyfinger dessert
directions: Line cake pan with waxed paper, a layer of ladyfingers, then a layer of egg, sugar, butter and lemon mixture, another layer of ladyfingers and another layer of the mixture.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese balls
directions: In mixing bowl, mash the cream cheese.
Mix in chopped dry beef and chopped onions.
Sprinkle and mix in Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and form into balls and refrigerate.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: potato omelette
directions: Heat margarine in large skillet.
Add sliced potatoes, a few at a time; cook until lightly browned on both sides and nearly tender. Remove from skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook onion in same pan until golden.
With slotted spoon, remove onion from pan; add lemon juice to onion.
Return potatoes to pan.
Arrange tomatoes over potatoes; spread onion mixture over all.
Cover skillet; cook over low heat for 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Beat eggs, cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon salt; pour eggs over vegetables in skillet.
Cover and cook on low heat until eggs are set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, flour, Raisin Bran, soda and salt in a large bowl. In a separate bowl, mix eggs, buttermilk and butter.
Combine the two mixtures.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake at 350° in 9 x 12 pan for 35 minutes.

title: light 'n tasty crepes
directions: Beat the eggs, then blend well with all other ingredients until batter is smooth and just thick enough to coat a spoon.
If batter is too thick, add a little more milk.
Cover and let stand at least 1/2 hour.
Heat a 5 to 6-inch frying pan or crepe pan. Oil lightly.
Cook on 1 side; turn and brown on the other side. Repeat until all batter is used.
As crepes are finished, stack with wax paper or foil between each.
Fill with fresh fruit as desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Boil pineapple.
Add orange gelatin; mix well to dissolve. Cool.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs with sugar and rest of ingredients. Sprinkle nutmeg on top before baking.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Done when knife placed in center comes out clean.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Combine in saucepan; cook until just thick enough.
Cool and spread.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Mix cheese with sausage.
Spoon onto muffin half.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake for 22 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean at 350°.
Use Fluffy Frosting to ice cake.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Fry sausage and beef; drain well. Add onion. Stir in melted cheese, soup and sauce. Put in crock-pot and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Chop onion and celery in food processor.
Cook rice and broccoli and drain.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add all ingredients to onion mixture, except bread crumbs; cook a few minutes.
Pour in casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 (8-inch) plastic flower pot, plastic flowers and garden trowel.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into hot deep fat. Remove when golden brown and drain on paper towel.

title: candied violets
directions: Wash the violets, including their stems.
In a bowl, beat egg whites with a wire whisk until frothy.
Place sugar in another bowl.
Taking one at a time, pick it up by the stem and dip into the egg whites, covering all surfaces.
Gently dip into the sugar, again being sure all of the petals, top and bottom, are covered. Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets; snip off stems.
Using a toothpick, open the petals to their original shape.
Sprinkle sugar on any uncoated areas.
Dry in a 200° oven for 30-40 minutes or until the sugar crystallizes.
Gently remove violets to wire racks with a spatula or two-tined fork.
Sprinkle again with sugar if violets appear syrupy.
Cool. Store in an airtight container with waxed paper between layers.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Then roll in crumbs, cheese and garlic salt mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a shallow baking dish, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add spinach last.
Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar; cream well. Add unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put Kiss in.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except sugar.
Blend thoroughly. Shape into small balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in sugar. Store in lightly covered container.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, powders, salt and soda; set aside.
Sift powdered sugar.
Mix oil, peanut butter and butter and blend.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add in powders.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with a fork and space onto greased cookie sheet.
Place into oven preheated at 350°.
Cook at least 12 minutes.

title: curried egg-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Carefully remove stem end of each chilled, peeled tomato.
Cut each tomato into four or six sections, almost to the stem end. Spread apart slightly.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Make a bed of salad greens on each plate and center a tomato on each.
Blend together mayonnaise, curry powder and salt.
Coarsely chop the eggs.
Mix into mayonnaise with celery, olives and onion.
Fill tomatoes with the egg mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes a nice, light lunch on a hot day served with Brown 'N Serve rolls and butter.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown
beef
and garlic until meat loses its red color, then drain.
Add
remaining
ingredients
and
stir.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until chili is desired thickness, about 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie(it makes its own crust.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender, on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 more minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: angel hair pasta salad
directions: You may want to delete some of these vegetables and add your own.
I like black olives, chopped.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix hot water, cornstarch and sugar and bring to boil.
Add peach jello.
Mix well.
Add sliced fresh peaches to hot jello mixture and pour into pie shell.
Chill and serve with dollops of Cool Whip.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken breast.
Beat egg and water together.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then coat with potato flakes.
Place chicken on foil lined pan.
Drizzle margarine over each piece. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400 about 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not turn chicken during cooking.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix 1 C sugar, baking powder, milk and flour and pour into buttered pan. Add 1 pint cherries and 1 C sugar on top. Pour boiling water over all and bake about 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend ingredients and put chips in last blend.
Drop by spoonful 2-inches apart on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add vanilla and water and stir.
Mix in 2 eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoons onto baking trays.
Bake for about 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool on rack.

title: wiener bean pot
directions: Combine all in a casserole dish or bean pot. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: missouri fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry.
Make paste of Italian dressing, flour, salt, lemon juice and butter.
Brush on chicken.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Add other ingredients. Mix well and bake in mini muffin tins for approximately 12 to 14 minutes at 375°. Makes 48.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate. Yields 35 servings.

title: three-herb pizza
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, prepare Sicilian Pizza Dough. Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pizza crust 15 minutes or until lightly browned on top. Remove from oven. Top crust with sliced cheese and then herbs.
Return pizza to oven and bake until cheese just melts.
Garnish with fresh herbs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheesy chicken
directions: Cook macaroni.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour, salt, pepper and mustard until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese, macaroni and chicken.
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook celery, onion and green peppers in butter over low heat until tender, not browned.
Blend bread and seasonings.
Add celery, onion and green peppers; toss lightly.
Pour broth over; mix.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: mexican style beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil with onion and garlic; drain.
Add water and seasonings; cover and simmer 1 hour, or until meat is tender. Stir together the sour cream and flour.
Stir into meat with mushrooms.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes.
