Serve over hot noodles.
Sprinkle with snipped chives or parsley.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a lasagna pan with graham crackers (bottom and 4 sides). Mix 2 packages of pudding and 3 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 mixture over graham crackers.
Then add a layer of graham crackers.
Pour rest of mixture in, then a last layer of graham crackers.

title: apple orchard punch
directions: In large punch bowl combine apple juice, cranberry cocktail concentrate and orange juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Thinly slice apple.
Float apple slices on top of punch.

title: triscuit appetizers
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put on crackers. Put on cookie sheet and bake until cheese melts.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into freezer can.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: easy tupperware bread
directions: Measure 10 cups flour into big (Fix-N-Mix) bowl.
In large bowl, mix dry yeast with warm water.
Add sugar, salt and eggs. Seal, burp and shake until mixed.
Make a well in flour with large mixing bowl.
Pour liquid mixture into well.
Do not stir.
Seal Fix-N-Mix bowl.
Burp and place in sink in very hot water.
Seal will pop in 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from sink.
Add 1/3 cup oleo, melted.
Stir with wooden spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Seal and replace in hot water.
Seal will pop in about 15 minutes.
Remove from sink.
Bake rolls at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 2 loaves or 3 dozen rolls.

title: onion cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onion tops, Accent, Worcestershire sauce and bacon bits all together.
Form a ball.
Roll in bacon bits.

title: buttermilk pancakes(mixed in bowl)
directions: Shake dry ingredients in a sealed plastic bowl.
Remove cover and add remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Spray cooking pan with nonstick cooking spray and heat.
Spread batter onto hot griddle; turn when upper side of pancake is bubbly.
Using wide spatula, flip only once.
Stack and place in warm oven until ready to serve.

title: no bake strawberry cheese cake
directions: For the crust, combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar; press into bottom and sides of 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: unbaked drop cookies
directions: Bring to a boil and let boil rapidly for 1/2 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup chunky peanut butter.
Add 3 cups of quick oats.
Drop quickly on waxed paper by tablespoon and let cool.

title: crackly ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and molasses and beat until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: valentine spritz
directions: Puree strawberries.
Combine all ingredients in tall glass and stir well.
Add enough ice to fill glass.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel and slice 6 cups pears and cover with water.
Add sugar and lemon; cook slowly for 4 hours (or until fruit is light colored).
Makes 2 to 3 pints.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in baking dish. Cover with bacon. Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: deer steak
directions: Take desired amount of deer steak; chop with edge of saucer. Salt, pepper and flour each piece; drop in hot skillet.
Cook until done.
Call me when it is ready.

title: walnut cherry cake
directions: Coarsely chop 1/4 cup of walnuts; set aside.
Chop remainder medium fine.
As package directs, prepare cake mix, adding vanilla and 3/4 cup walnuts.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Cool 10 minutes; invert out onto wire racks until cooled.
Fold food coloring into topping.
Spread a 1-inch wide ring of topping on outer edge layer plate.
Spread remaining topping on side of cake. Sprinkle reserved walnuts on cake top.
Chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine butter, ketchup, Durkee, Tabasco, salt, pepper, chili pepper and red pepper in pot over low heat.
Cook until butter is melted and sauce is warm.
(If too spicy, add ketchup.
If you like it hotter, add Tabasco.)

title: chicken fire cracker
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and cheese.
Blend well.
Fill hot dog rolls with chicken mixture.
Wrap in aluminum foil, twisting the end to resemble fire crackers.
Place on grill.
Heat about 20 minutes, turning several times.
Makes 8. This can be done in microwave. Wrap in wax paper instead of tinfoil.
This is great to make ahead of time and take in the coach.
Just keep in the fridge.
The filling can be changed to tuna, salmon, diced ham.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Place in 1 1/2-quart saucepan which has tight lid.
Cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Heat beans separately, drain and combine with onion and pepper.
Heat oil, vinegar and honey; pour over other ingredients. Mix and let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Keeps for several days.

title: bacon and eggs(recipe for kids to make.)
directions: Take a muffin tin, spray with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place a strip of bacon in each muffin tin hole.
Crack an egg and place egg on each strip of bacon.
Bake at 350° until bacon is brown and egg is done to consistency desired.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Divide dough into 10 portions.
Roll dough thin.
Fill with apple slices and place in baking dish.
Pour hot syrup over them and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
May put 6 red hots in each.

title: corn fritters
directions: Use fresh corn, cooked or raw.
Slice down the center of each row of kernels and with flat of knife, squeeze out the pulp.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Drop onto hot frying pan or griddle with a tablespoon.
Brown fritters on both sides.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets in covered saucepan with water until they are done, but not mushy.
Peel and slice them while hot. Keep warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; then add milk.
Cook until thickened. Add small amount of hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Then add egg mixture to hot mixture.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Take off stove, then add butter until melted.
Pour in pie shell.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with beans.
Cut chicken into pieces and place on top of beans.
Mix milk (or wine) with soup and spread over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with margarine and broth and spread over soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oven barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and shape into balls.
Combine flour and paprika.
Roll balls in flour mixture and brown in large skillet in oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Pour barbecue sauce over and place covered casserole in 350° oven.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Make 3 layers of all ingredients in greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: greek shrimp
directions: In skillet, saute celery and onions in margarine until limp. Add shrimp, rice, seasonings, cheese, olives and tomatoes. Transfer mixture to a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly and shrimp are done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix (except Tater Tots and grated cheese) and put in greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Spread in cake pan and bake at 400° for 9 minutes.

title: grandpa's beans
directions: Wash beans.
Put into a 6-quart pressure pot.
Cook in water at low pressure for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes or juice and ham.
Replace to burner and cook 1 1/4 more hours at low pressure.
More salt may be needed depending on saltiness of ham.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased casserole.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread nuts in bottom of pan and place frozen rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle all the dry pudding over rolls.
Boil butter and brown sugar; pour over pudding and rolls. Set in cool oven overnight or several hours until rolls have risen.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: delicious coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix, cook and serve in same pan.
Pour oil into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tilt pan until oil covers bottom. Combine cake mix, eggs and water in pan.
Stir with fork until blended, about 2 minutes.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until center springs back when touched.

title: 1, 2 or 3 alarm chili
directions: Lightly brown meat; add green onions and garlic.
Cook until onion is transparent (about 5 minutes).
Add green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes, Tabasco and salsa or jalapeno peppers (for 2 or 3 alarm).
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 1 to 2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add onion, garlic salt and spaghetti sauce. Simmer into sauce.

title: play doh
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil.
Mix.
Add boiling water.
Mix and knead.
Add flour until dough is not sticky.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple reserving juice.
Mix juice with cornstarch, sauce and mustard.
Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish, skin side up.
Broil until brown.
Stir sauce and pour over chicken. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Arrange lemon and pineapple slices around chicken.
Spoon sauce from baking pan over all.
Continue baking 5 minutes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix all together.
Can be stored in individual containers days ahead.
Great for weddings, showers, receptions, etc.
Some of same punch can be frozen in designer containers and added to punch bowl to keep punch cold.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in 1 quart casserole at 350°.
Good with ham.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in butter about 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in tomato sauce, water, bay leaf, parsley and salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add additional water if needed. Add thawed shrimp.
(Can start Minute rice at this point.)
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cook, covered, over medium heat 5 minutes. Serve shrimp creole over rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: amazing quiche
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
In a blender container, combine milk, eggs, flour, onion, marjoram and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover; blend 15 seconds.
Pour into pie plate. Top with cheeses.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple puddingwestboro, missouri
directions: Cook until clear.
Remove from fire and stir in beaten yolks of 2 eggs, then fold in beaten whites and 1 c.
pineapple chunks. Set in slow oven in a buttered baking dish for 20 minutes.
When cool, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip and pineapple dices.

title: savory chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken. Drizzle melted oleo over the stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: country grits and sausage
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; stir in grits.
Return to boil. Reduce heat.
Cook 4 minutes.
Combine grits and cheese in a large bowl.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: wrva snow cream
directions: Blend and pour over 2 quarts fresh snow.

title: pretty congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving juice.
Add juice to gelatin in a saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend sour cream into gelatin mixture. Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold or 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Unmold or cut in squares.
Serve on salad greens.
This is a very colorful salad as well as delicious.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with whole crackers.
Mix 1 package pudding with 2 cups milk.
Fold in 4 ounces Cool Whip over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and repeat.
Add a third layer.
Frost with chocolate frosting, stirred gently.
Chill for several hours.

title: hundred dollar cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add dissolved cocoa.
Next add the eggs, flour, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until done.
Top with icing.

title: almond slices
directions: Grate nuts; do not grind!
Put nuts, flour and sugar in bowl. Blend in margarine with fingers or pastry blender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 2 long blocks, 2 inches square. Wrap in wax paper; chill or freeze overnight.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove at once to racks to cool.
Yields 5 dozen.
Store in airtight containers.
Will not ship well.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb with 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons butter and place in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Let stand while mixing 1 cup sugar, salt, 1 cup flour, large egg (beaten), baking powder and oatmeal.
Place on top of rhubarb mixture and shake down through.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti; drain.
Add vegetables (cut up).
Add Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Toss everything together good.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Ready to eat.

title: dilly potato salad
directions: Wash and boil potatoes until tender.
When cool enough to handle, peel and chop potatoes (the secret is to mix this salad while the potatoes are still warm).
Add remaining ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour, alternating whipping cream.
Add flavoring.
Bake in pound cake pan.
Start in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: patrice's haystacks
directions: Melt morsels over very low heat or use double boiler.
Mix in noodles and peanuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoons onto wax paper. Cool.
(I break up the noodles and chop the peanuts coarsely; they hold together better.)

title: taco plate
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in refried beans and seasoning.
Using a 13 x 9 inch pan, spread hamburger mixture over bottom. Spread all of the sour cream onto next layer. Then, layer picante sauce and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with tostado chips.

title: mini marvels
directions: Beat eggs; add pecans and dates.
Spoon into greased mini tins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 small treats.
You must use mini tins.

title: lubia polo
directions: Heat olive oil in large frying pan.
Add meat, onions and seasonings and saute until the meat is brown.
Add water, tomato sauce and beans to meat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve meat dish over rice.
It's even better the next day.

title: pizza dips
directions: Brown meat in frying pan.
Drain excess fat.
Combine flour, cheese, herbs and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add sausage.
Mix until evenly distributed.
Sprinkle with ice water and stir until dough is just moist enough to handle.

title: cheesy tortillas
directions: Fry tortillas and onions in 3 tablespoons oil in a large frying pan.
Scramble eggs and milk; pour over tortillas and toss quickly.
Add cheese and continue to toss.
Add salt and pepper and diced tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes on low heat.
Serve with Mexican style beans.

title: mama's peanut butter bonbons
directions: In a saucepan, melt peanut butter and butter.
In a large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill until firm.
In separate double boilers, melt butterscotch and chocolate pieces.
Dip candy balls in butterscotch and place on wax paper.
Dip candy balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: fruit of the bayou
directions: Make white sauce with milk, flour and butter. Add seafood. Saute celery, bell pepper, parsley and green onions in a little butter. Add sherry, mushrooms, egg yolks (whipped) and seasonings. Combine with cream sauce and fish. Fold in grated cheese. Bake in a greased casserole with buttered crumbs on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° until bread crumbs lightly brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: green apple sorbet
directions: Combine apples and fresh lemon juice in medium bowl.
Cover with plastic and freeze overnight.
Combine water and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat and boil.
Cool completely.
Puree frozen apples and sugar syrup in processor until mixture is as smooth as possible.
Transfer apple mixture to ice cream maker and process according to instructions. Transfer sorbet to container and freeze.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring Coke to boil, adding all ingredients.
Cook until cream cheese is soft.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.

title: dough wrapped cream cheese appetizer
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; pinch seams of 4 rolls together to form a rectangle.
Place cream cheese block on dough; sprinkle with basil.
Wrap dough around cream cheese; pinch seams to seal. Place block wrapped with dough on baking sheet with seam down. Brush top of dough with egg; bake 20 minutes or until brown in 400° oven.
Serve with crackers.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Mix and cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, then molasses.
Next, add dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls about the size of marbles.
Dip in sugar. (Do Not Flatten.)
Cook 350° - 15 minutes.

title: one dish cabbage rolls
directions: Cut up cabbage and place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Brown meat and onions, add seasonings and salt to taste.
Simmer and drain.
Add rice, soup and water, tomato sauce, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Place over cabbage (do not stir), cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill for at least one hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice and milk to boil; stir well all the time.
Add other ingredients, sprinkling nutmeg on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Melt margarine. Mix together. Add remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for an hour.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add sour cream. Stir in sugar, 2 Tbsp. flour, vanilla and salt. Mix well. Stir in apples.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar. Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks; beat well. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla, then coconut and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased and floured 8 or 9 inch cake pans. Bake at 325 for 25 minutes.

title: nappa salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and store in a plastic bag.

title: classic tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a small saucepan, combine soup mix and water.
Heat to boiling.
In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter; blend in flour and pepper.
Gradually stir in hot soup and cook until thickened.
Add tuna and fold in peas.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 15 minutes until heated through.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, judging the amount of vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper according to your taste.
Chill well before serving.
It should be creamy and tangy.

title: quick ham casserole
directions: Combine butter and onion powder.
Stir into corn flakes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine corn,
sour
cream,
eggs
and	oil; beat well. Combine cornmeal
and
baking powder.
Stir into corn mixture. Pour into a
greased 10-inch skillet or pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients, adding Cool Whip last. Sprinkle orange jello over mixture; stir well until blended. Spoon mixture into large bowl and refrigerate.

title: chocolate icebox cookies
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts; spread in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Chill well.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip; spread over first layer.
Combine pudding, milk and vanilla; spread over cheese layer.
Spread 1 cup Cool Whip on top of chocolate pudding. Sprinkle with chopped nuts or chocolate swirls.
Chill well.

title: sluggers surprise
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine water and ice to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin; stir until slightly thickened. Remove unmelted ice.
Add fruit and chill 10 minutes, until thickened.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple with juice, and sugar together. Simmer mixture for 5 minutes. Add cream cheese and baby food. Stir until cream cheese is smooth. Refrigerate until mixture starts to gel. Then whip evaporated milk until fluffy and add to mixture. Sprinkle with nuts and chill.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes with an electric mixer.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Blend well.
Chill for 30 minutes before serving on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blackberry bar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add oats and 1/4 cup water.
Mix until crumbly.
Firmly pat half the mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: hip padders
directions: Combine milk, chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons butter.
Heat over hot water until melted.
Stir in nuts and 1 tablespoon of vanilla.
Set aside.
Cream 1 cup of butter and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press 2/3 of mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate filling.
Sprinkle remaining oatmeal mixture over top and more chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: recipe for love
directions: Mix together and bake until sweet and tender. Serve daily.

title: pizzaiola sauce(place on steak or steak sandwich)
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer.
Place on steak or on steak sandwiches.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add milk,
flour and baking powder.
Blend well.
Fold in the 2 cups of blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups half full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: no bake fudge brownies
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.
Add sweetened milk, wafer crumbs and 1/2 cup nuts; stir until well blended.
Press into foil-lined 8-inch square pan. Press remaining nuts over the top.
Let stand until set.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: sate ayam (chicken satay indonesian style)
directions: You will need barbecue sticks (bamboo skewers).

title: peach-topped pastry
directions: Put 1 cup of the flour in a mixing bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup of the margarine to form even crumbs.
With a fork, lightly mix in about 2 tablespoons water to form a moist dough.
Press dough out on a greased baking sheet to shape into a thin strip, 12 to 15-inches long and 3 to 5-inches wide.

title: banana slush
directions: In large saucepan heat water and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir in orange juice concentrate, pineapple juice and bananas.
Place in three 2-quart containers; freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 20 minutes or until mixture can be spooned.
To serve, stir in ginger ale.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Layer beans with onion and pepper.
Put meat on top, then pour barbecue sauce over top.
Use crock-pot; cook on low overnight.
Do not stir until ready to remove from pot.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: cherry crumbles
directions: Spread pie filling in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan; sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
(Do not stir.)
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden.
This can be done in a reflector oven or in a Dutch oven.

title: candied dills
directions: Remove and reserve half the pickles from their container. Pour approximately 1/2 the sugar over the pickles.
Pour in 1 tablespoon pickling spice and 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon.
Repeat with remaining pickles, sugar, pickling spice and cinnamon.
Seal the jar and refrigerate.
Turn approximately every six hours for 24 hours to help dissolve the sugar.
Serve when the sugar has dissolved.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Peel and dice potato.
Set aside.
Slice carrot and celery stick.
Set aside.
Pour milk into large enough kettle.
Add oysters and vegetables to milk.
Add optional butter or margarine. Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: canned okra
directions: Mix all together. Use enough water to see in pan. Bring to boil. When okra changes color pack in jars and seal. When ready to eat, open jar.
Rinse with cold water, drain. Fry as fresh okra. Don't re-salt.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Cook frozen chopped broccoli; drain and lay in buttered, shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Over this, pour cream of chicken soup as it comes from the can.
Rinse each can with 3 tablespoons of milk and pour this over the soup.
Top with 1/2-inch stuffing. Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks and milk in a 2-quart bowl.
Mix well and cook 3 minutes on High; remove and stir well with a wire whisk.
Return to microwave and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring well after each minute, until thickened.
Remove and add vanilla; allow to stand 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer pudding, wafers and bananas. Top with meringue and place in a conventional oven for 5 minutes until top is browned.

title: harvest molasses cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and spices together.
Cream butter or margarine; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add pumpkin, walnuts and fruits.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° for 65 minutes or until done.
Cool thoroughly. Frost with Orange Butter Cream Frosting.

title: mildred's fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and syrup.
Stir well. Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, to prevent sticking.
(I use long handle wooden spoon.)
When boils down, check in tap water.
See if it feels like chewing gum, or use candy thermometer at 238°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until almost done.
Slice and arrange sweet potatoes in baking dish.
In small saucepan, over medium heat, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all together with an 8 ounce jar Miracle Whip.
May add chicken or ham pieces. Set overnight.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix with electric mixer all ingredients until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch size).
Bake at 400° until set, firm and light brown.

title: turkey and asparagus fajitas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Warm tortillas in foil 10 minutes. Combine turkey, asparagus, dressing and cumin in medium size bowl. Let stand for 15 minutes; drain.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add drained turkey mixture; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes or until asparagus is tender.
Stir in tomato.
Make sure turkey is done, too.
Unwrap tortillas.
Spoon turkey mixture down center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle cheese.
Roll up.
Serve with salsa, light sour cream or yogurt and shredded lettuce, if desired.

title: grilled honey-mustard pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork chops. Grill over medium heat for about 20 minutes, brushing with the honey mixture each time you turn them.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chocolate bar 1 to 2 minutes on 50% power in microwave. Stir in rice cereal and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: meat casserole
directions: Place
uncooked meat in oblong dish.
Boil macaroni for 10 minutes.
Drain and add to meat in even layers.
Add butter.
Pour soup and water over mixture and sprinkle with salt and cheese. Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Defrost spinach; set aside.
Take chicken breasts and flatten until thin. Season both sides to taste.
Place 1 or 2 tablespoons chopped spinach on each breast half.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place chicken rolls in nonstick skillet and cook, turning until cooked.
Place the rest of the spinach in skillet and pour tomato sauce over all.
Cook 5 or 10 minutes longer. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Cover until cheese melts.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2 people.

title: cocktail crabmeat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 4 hours before serving. Serve cold with an assortment of crackers or homemade Melba toast. Yields 20 to 30 servings.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in a small mixing bowl; blend in sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set (pie will not test done).
Cool.
Cut into wedges. Serve topped with ice cream and hot fudge sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Sift all dry ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender until it resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk all at once. Stir until dough follows fork around bowl. If it seems too dry, add a small amount of milk to mixture. Turn dough out on lightly floured surface. Knead gently. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes.

title: butter torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture with vanilla.
Grease two 9-inch cake pans and line with wax paper.
Put batter in and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pans.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 325°.
Add marshmallows and return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes until slightly brown.
Cool completely.

title: white salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a dish; chill 2 hours.
May be topped with cherries to add color.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Fry hamburger and drain. Put hamburger in medium sized pot. Mix all the ingredients with hamburger in pot.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook box of stuffing shells by directions on box, drain. When mix is simmered, take a spoon and fill your shells.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with garlic bread if desired. Great to freeze for later.

title: snow ice cream
directions: In a 2-quart bowl mix beaten eggs and milk.
Blend in sugar; mixing well.
Add vanilla, salt and flavoring if desired.
Put into a gallon container and gradually add snow; mixing well until of desired consistency.
Serve immediately or freeze.

title: fresno potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 3-quart pan; cover with water.
Boil; cook covered for 20 minutes.
Drain, cool and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In greased shallow 2-quart casserole, arrange 1/2 potatoes and top with 1/2 bacon and onion.
Stir milk into sour cream, spread 1/2 mixture over onion, then 1/2 cheese; season. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Drizzle with butter all over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add sausages and stir until coated. Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: reeder refrigerator rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in small bowl.
Let stand until softened.
Pour scalded milk over Crisco, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir until Crisco is melted.
Stir in mashed potatoes.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Add softened yeast.
Mix well.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Combine reserved pineapple juice, cranberry juice and lemon juice in a medium saucepan.

Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add gelatin, stirring until it is completely dissolved. Refrigerate until mixture begins to set. Stir in pineapple and celery. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken puff pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dinner rolls into 8 triangles. Place 2 triangles, one on top of the other.
Press slightly. Repeat with remaining dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 12 minutes.
In large saucepan, heat cream of chicken soup, mixed vegetables and poultry seasoning until bubbly.
Fold in chunk chicken.
Spoon hot mixture into a 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
Place triangles on mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: parmesan cocktail biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix, 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, chives and oregano.
Cut 1/4 cup cold margarine into 1/4-inch pieces.
Add margarine pieces to baking mix and toss with fork until coated.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: jello pudding cake
directions: Mix well and put in a greased pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Combine dry ingredients in small bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Pat crumbs on to coat.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 36.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Put drained pineapple in 2-quart casserole. Combine sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pineapple. Sprinkle on grated cheese, then crackers.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: african meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, pork, cracker meal, eggs, onion, salt, pepper, 1 1/4 cup peanuts and brown sugar.
Combine remaining peanuts and brown sugar.
Grease 9-inch loaf pan heavily; line bottom and sides with brown sugar mixture.
Fill with meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn out carefully onto platter, glazed side up.
Serves 8 to 10.
I spray with Pam spray before greasing.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Blend honey and milk together.
Add flour gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt; mix well.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute minced onions, garlic and parsley in margarine until soft; do not brown.
Add tomato paste. Stir well and cook for a few minutes.
Add shrimp and seasonings. Cook about 20 minutes.
Thicken slightly with cornstarch.
Serves 8.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Melt butter, add flour until blended.
Add 2 cups broth, milk and cream slowly.
Cook until it thickens.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Add remaining 3 cups broth and chicken.
Serve with sliced avocado, grated Monterey Jack cheese and tortilla chips crunched on top of individual servings.

title: new potato bake
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream, hot pepper sauce, potatoes and onions.
Spread in greased 2-quart baking dish evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix salt and flour and add milk gradually to form a smooth paste.
Then add eggs and beat 2 minutes.
Put in hot greased pan about 1/2-inch deep.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300° or 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate outrage snack cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter or margarine, oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, eggs, walnuts and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread batter in an 8-inch square micro-safe pan.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on High 4 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn; microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until top appears dry and bottom is an even color. Sprinkle remaining chips over top of warm cake.
Let stand 10 minutes and spread evenly over cake.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables, cover with water in a large pot.
Add onion soup mix, bouillon, or other condiments.
No salt.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are done.
Eat anytime you feel hungry, as often and as much as you like.

title: venison pot roast with vegetables
directions: Lard the roast well by inserting cubes of salt pork into small cuts in the roast.
Heat butter in a Dutch oven or deep casserole and brown the meat on all sides.
Add hot water, fruit juice, celery, parsley, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer gently for 3 hours on top of the stove or in oven at 350°, until meat is tender.
If liquid gets too low, add water.
About 1 hour before meal is to be served, add peeled potatoes, carrots and onions. Add a little additional salt for vegetables.
When vegetables are tender, remove them and the meat to a platter and keep hot. Thicken liquid with 2 to 3 tablespoons flour.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Put in a Dutch oven and cover.
Sprinkle tapioca over vegetables.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not uncover until done.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil water and bouillon.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces. Add to water.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add flour; stir in bouillon water.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add Cheez Whiz; stir until melted.
Never let boil after you add the flour mixture, or it may curdle.

title: party punch
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Bring to boil.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients (except ginger ale).
Chill well.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Add mint or pieces of candy to glass.

title: creamy strawberry-lemon squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter until well blended.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup milk until blended. Spread over crust.
Pour 2 3/4 c. milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Blend well.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Cover with whipped topping. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight before cutting.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Remove extra fat from ham. Wash beans and put in pot with ham and veggies. Cover with water.
Cook until meat falls off ham end.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine and mix.
Pat out on floured board.
Cut and put in lightly greased pan.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen rolls.

title: special refried beans(microwave)
directions: In 1-quart microwave-safe dish, combine beans, seasoning mix and water.
Mix.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on Medium 7 to 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Top with cheese and onion before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: amazing glob stoppers
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave on Low, or in double boiler.
Add peanut butter, Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in muffin cups (half full).
Refrigerate.
Very good snack.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat eggs and add to butter mixture. Mix in vanilla and lemon extracts. Mix nutmeg with flour. Alternately add flour and milk. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. Roll out on a floured board about 1/4 of dough at a time, about 1/4-inch thick. Cut and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all.
Pour into a large (13 x 8 1/2) greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scottish short bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Stir in egg yolk and vanilla. Gradually add flour, mixing with fingers.
Add chopped pecans if desired.
Spread mixture evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prick with fork to form squares.
Cook in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until just golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cool in pan.
This freezes nicely and thaws in about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and frosting. Reserve 1/3 of this mix.
Add chips to remaining cream cheese mixture and spread over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Spread refrigerated (reserved) cream cheese mix over top.
Cut into bars.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles as directed; rinse and drain.
Brown beef in butter.
Add salt, garlic salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and onions. Alternate layer of noodles, mixture and meat in greased 2-quart casserole, beginning with noodles and ending with meat.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted or browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes, turning two or three times.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: semi-hot peppers
directions: Arrange peppers in jars.
In a pot, bring to boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over peppers; seal.

title: grape-nut custard
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: fern's fabulous fudge
directions: You will need a sifter, a large bowl, a rubber spatula and 3 pans.

title: perfect "fudgy" brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and shortening together in small saucepan over low heat.
Pour over sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Once mixed, stir in remaining ingredients. Spread batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overbake. Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 32 small bars.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
In casserole dish spread onion mixture, top with rice and broccoli; add milk, then cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix everything together.
The longer it sets the better.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Layer beef, onion, potatoes, carrots and celery in roaster or crock-pot.
Mix soup with one can of water and tapioca, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over all. Add bay leaf if desired.
Bake covered at 250° for 5 hours.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Mix flour,
baking powder, salt and shortening together well, then add hot water.
Mix and roll out as desired.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add other ingredients.
Put in greased pie pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water and boil 1 minute.
Set aside until cool.
Add 1 cup cottage cheese, 1 cup miniature marshmallows and 1 cup pineapple.
Let jell.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix in eggs and oil. Add carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops until they are brown on both sides. Take out of skillet. Cut onion into little slices and lay on bottom of 9 x 12 inch pan. Slice potatoes and place on top of onions. Then place pork chops on top of potatoes. Pour both cans of mushroom soup on top of the pork chops. Spread evenly. Cover with aluminum foil. Cook in oven at 375 degrees for 1 hour. Take out. Let stand for 10 minutes. Serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a air tight container. Use 2 to 3 tablespoons to a coffee mug of hot water.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter. Add flour and salt which have been sifted together. Add flavoring (1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon almond extract). Cream mixture until very light and fluffy; the longer, the better. In a large bowl, combine eggs and baking powder. Beat lightly. Add sugar gradually while beating constantly and beat until sugar is dissolved and mixture is satin smooth. Combine mixtures and beat with an electric mixer until well blended or very long time by hand. Bake at 325° until done! Use large tube pan.

title: homemade chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and add enough Miracle Whip to make salad moist.

title: banana bread
directions: Slice bananas into a mixer bowl and beat well.
Add baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
In a separate bowl, mix together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine with banana mixture and beat well.
(Can add 1/4 cup raisins dusted with 1 tablespoon flour, if desired.
We like it best without raisins.)
Bake in 2 buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pans for about 45 minutes.
(Recipe can be halved to make 1 loaf.)

title: orange juice cookies
directions: Mix all together and form in small balls.
Roll in coconut or finely chopped pecans.

title: easy pie crust (double crust)(no rolling)
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil together.
Add water and mix.
Divide dough.
With fingers, spread dough in the pie pan.

title: pay day bars
directions: Bring sugar and light Karo to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/3 cups peanut butter, vanilla and salted peanuts.
Stir and pour mixture over Rice Krispies cereal.
Mix and then press in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes and place in a glass microwave dish arranging potato wedges into one layer in dish. Salt to taste and place slices of butter over the potatoes. Cover with a glass top and cook until done. Our Microwave is a 700 watt. For two servings (3 medium potatoes)
cooking times is about 8 minutes.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for several hours to blend all flavors.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, pecans and salt together in a pot and cook on small burner, stirring constantly.
When it comes to a boil, cook for 12 minutes.
Drop a pecan into cold water.
If it is hard, then it is done.
Stir in baking soda, it will foam up. Pour thin coat on aluminum foil.
Do not spread out with spoon. After it cools, break into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts. Put half of dressing mix in a large dish.
Place chicken on top. Pour stock over chicken and add rest of dressing mix on top. Bake at 325° until bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: peach custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Put 1/2 peaches to cover crust in bottom. Pour custard mixture over peaches. Bake till custard thickens. Can use berries instead of peaches.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large casserole dish; stir well. Add cut up chicken and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: frontier beans
directions: Do not drain beans.
Brown all meat and chopped onions.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350° or in crock-pot for 3 hours.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix pudding together as directed on box. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots on the diagonal or in crinkles, then blanch until crisp-tender (6 to 8 minutes).
Add green pepper and onion. Mix together all other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
This will keep up to 10 days.

title: valentine cookie frosting
directions: Melt milk, candies and butter together.
Add to powdered sugar.
Allow to cool.
Spread on sugar cookies.
Enjoy!

title: spanish rolls
directions: Cook meat with all of the ingredients except the rolls.
Drain and set meat mixture aside.
Cut tops off of rolls and pull the inside breading out.
Stuff bread rolls.
Wrap individually in foil and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
If frozen, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in partly thawed strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into 8-cup ring mold and refrigerate until firm.
Keep remaining half of gelatin at room temperature.
Beat room temperature cream cheese until well softened.
Add dairy sour cream and salt and beat until smooth.
Carefully spread in an even layer over firm, chilled gelatin in mold.
Return to refrigerator.
When remaining portion of gelatin begins to thicken, spoon it over the cream cheese layer.
Chill overnight or not less than 4 hours.
Unmold onto serving dish and garnish with well-drained pineapple slices. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 items, then add mayonnaise and sour cream. Mix and chill several hours.
Serve on a plate of lettuce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients, except nuts.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce cake(diet)
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in Sweet 'N Low brown gradually.
Add applesauce.
Add flour, sifted with soda, salt and spices.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spread in a buttered and floured 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: molasses apple baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat 1/4 cup water or broth in a skillet over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir for 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add water, if needed, during this process.
Add apples and cover.
Lower heat and cook for 5 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put fruit (pineapple, cherries and coconut) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take a fork and swirl the fruit over the bottom of pan.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and butter with a fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of fruit.
Bake 1 hour.
Can be served plain or topped with whipped cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Follow directions on taco dinner box.
After done, layer taco mix, cheese and crumbled taco shells.
Bake until cheese is melted and salad is hot.
Serve over lettuce and tomatoes.

title: congealed waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water. Add cold water and lemon juice. Chill until thickened but not set. Stir in apples, celery and nuts. Chill until firm. Make dressing of mayonnaise mixed with enough honey to make consistency of salad dressing. Serve with the congealed salad.

title: scramble
directions: Bake in very slow oven (250°) for 2 hours, stirring and turning mixture with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.
Makes 9 quarts.

title: clam's n' white sauce
directions: Start 3 hours before dinner by putting clams in freezer. (they open real easy about 5 minutes before you start).
Open the clams into the bowl reserving all the clam liquid.
Start linguini water.
Crush and chop garlic, the finer the better. Chop parsley.
Rinse clams in clam juice by dunking them, this should remove any shell, dirt, or pearls.
Chop clams fine.
In skillet saute garlic, parsley in olive oil and butter.
Before the garlic starts to brown, carefully pour in the clam liquid.
Make sure you leave the sand and shell pieces on the bottom of bowl. Mix cornstarch using only enough water to dissolve and make smooth.
Add cornstarch to ingredients stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Turn off heat.
Add chopped clams and serve with linguini immediatly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up broccoli and arrange with florets toward center.
Cover and microwave on High until tender (about 6 minutes).
Mix oil, garlic, vinegar, salt and seasonings.
Pour over broccoli. Microwave butter on High until melted.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle over broccoli.

title: ruth decker's apple crisp
directions: Put apples in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly, then press firmly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes with onion. Add salt, pepper and flour. Fry in vegetable oil until crisp; drain.

title: cream of corn and crab soup
directions: Put chicken stock, corn and sliced onion in top of double boiler and cook over boiling water until onion is soft.
Press all this through a sieve (all the corn husk won't go through).
Put into top of double boiler.
Add cream and flaked crab meat.
Heat over boiling water.
Add blended flour and butter, stirring until creamy.
Add seasonings.
If desired, 1 or 2 teaspoons sugar may be added.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: pea casserole
directions: Saute the onion and celery.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Boil noodles as directed on box.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except for sauce and extra cheese.
Put about 2 or 3 spoonfuls of mixture onto the noodles and roll.
Continue until there are no more noodles.
Put into a lightly greased baking dish (I use Pam).
Pour sauce over it and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top with remaining cheese and let sit until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken
until meat falls off bone.
Cut meat into bite size
pieces, reserving 2 cups of broth.
Melt butter and mix into dressing.
Combine soups and 2 cups broth.

title: nacho dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream in bowl.
Stir in bean dip, seasoning mix, Tabasco sauce, taco sauce and half of each cheese. Spoon into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield:
96 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Heat butter, water, cocoa and shortening in saucepan until it comes to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; stir by hand until mixed.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla; mix well. Bake in a large cookie sheet pan that has at least 1-inch sides. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, make the icing.

title: rosy rhubarb salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook and stir rhubarb and sugar over medium-low heat until rhubarb is soft and tender.
Remove from the heat, add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juices.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in apples, celery and pecans.
Pour into a 4 1/2 cup mold or glass bowl.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grilled cornish hens
directions: Place charcoal around drip pan.
Wash hens.
Pat dry and rub onion salt in and on hens.
Place hens over medium coals.
Baste hens often with mixture.
Grill until tender, turning often.

title: cheese-potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns; add all ingredients, except corn flakes. Mix well.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken chevre patisserie
directions: Skin, wash, salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Place tablespoon of cheese on each chicken breast and fold pastry around chicken, pinch seams together and seal.
Make decorative tops with a small cookie cutter.
Place on top of the chicken breasts.
Brush with beaten egg.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Peel, devein and boil shrimp. Rinse.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and pat dry. Chop shrimp into small pieces and add to mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add a small amount of lemon juice. Dip is better after a day or two. Serve with crackers. Serves 50.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring carrots to a boil and drain.
Combine other ingredients. Boil 5 minutes and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate.
Will keep long time.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and clean out. Set in baking dish. Mix all other ingredients saving 1/3 of tomato sauce. Pack meat mixture into peppers; pour the remaining tomato sauce over the tops of peppers. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil; add meat and cook until done.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce, sauce mix and V-8 juice.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer 15 minutes.
Cover bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with a thin layer of meat sauce, add a layer each of uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used ending with meat sauce.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when done.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook onion and pepper in broth where chicken has been cooked until tender.
Combine pepper, onion, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and tomatoes in a large bowl.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1 can of onions.
Put in greased glass casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining can of onions on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill pickles appetizers
directions: In a medium bowl mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion juice and grated onions. Spread the mixture thinly on the white bread slices. Roll 1 baby dill
pickle in each slice of bread.
Place in a medium glass baking dish with the seam side down. Cover and chill in the refrigerator 8 hours, or overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar.
Beat and add 1/2 cup of light cream.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell (9 to 10-inch size).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Before baking, add fresh grated nutmeg on top, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender; peel and cut to size.
Bring vinegar, water, sugar and spice to a boil.
Add beets; cook for 5 minutes. Pack and seal.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients together good.
Add water and oil.
Mix together.
Put in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until it forms into a ball, stirring constantly.
Do not overcook.
Food coloring may be added before or after cooking. Knead slightly on wax paper and let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: jello fluff
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in thawed Cool Whip.
May be served immediately or stored for 2 to 3 days.
For lighter version, use sugar free Jello, lite Cool Whip and low fat cottage cheese.
Add pecans if you wish.

title: cranberry christmas carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2-quart mold or loaf pan (may use 2 small loaf pans to give as Christmas gifts).
Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours for larger pan or 1 hour for small loaf pans or until top is browned and springs back when lightly touched.

title: never fail coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add all ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry bread
directions: In a bowl or food processor, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add the egg, orange juice and butter.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries, walnuts, mint and orange rind.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Remove skins.
Mash pulp, add remaining ingredients and whip until fluffy.
Place in a 1 qt ungreased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes, or until heated through.

title: homemade butter
directions: Pour whipping cream into jar.
Shake, shake, shake!
Shake until solid butter forms.
Spread on brrad or crackers.

title: sizzling salsa dip
directions: This recipe is so easy to make.
You can make as much as or as little as you want.

title: red mexican salsa
directions: Cut up cilantro.
Dice tomatoes and slice or dice jalapenos. Dice onion.
Mix all together and salt to taste.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Mix
sugar
and
eggs well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately
with
milk
and molasses.
Add dates, raisins and nuts.
Pour
into
greased	vegetable cans.
Partly cover cans with
aluminum foil.
Set in bottom of large kettle that has a good
cover.
Add 3-inches of water in kettle.
Cook on burner 1 1/2
hours.
Partly
cool;	carefully cut out the bottom of can and push it against the bread to remove from can.
Freezes good.

title: chili boats
directions: Cut rolls in half.
Indent the bottom of each roll with fingertips.
Put
a
small	amount of chili, approximately 1/2 teaspoon,
and
a
little
shredded
cheese on bottom of roll. Replace top
and
replace filled rolls on tray in bag.
Freeze until ready
to
serve.
To serve, remove tray from bag, place trays of rolls
in oven at 350° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serve warm. Makes 60 Chili Boats.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: You can prepare salad ahead using the following steps.

title: fudgie brownies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat very hard.
Stir in cocoa and flour, mixed together.
Stir like mad.
Fold in nuts and add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water, flour and nuts.
Work into soft ball.
Break off small pieces and shape into fingers or crescents. Bake at 300° to 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: creamy orange dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream until smooth; add orange juice and orange peel.
Serve with celery sticks, carrots or cauliflower.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix peas, beans, green pepper, celery, onion and pimento. Pour oil over these ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: tortilla chips
directions: Cut corn tortillas into 8 triangles each.
Place in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Coat tortilla pieces lightly with cooking spray and sprinkle with desired spices.
Bake in upper third of a 400° oven until lightly toasted, about 3 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Stir together broccoli, grapes, onions and bacon.
Mix dressing with salad just before serving.
Add slivered almonds.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples, oil, nuts and raisins.
Pour into two well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: 4 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: b.l.t. soup
directions: Saute bacon in medium-size saucepan until lightly browned.
Add celery and onion.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Drain off all excess fat.
Place vegetables and bacon in large pot.
Add tomato, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook, while stirring, until bubbly and thickened.
Add lettuce.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Crackers can be added to increase crunchiness.

title: pancakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend.
Can prepare the night before and refrigerate.

title: maui macjackers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook slowly over medium heat. Stir gently until mixture boils.
Continue cooking until mixture reaches hard texture when dropped in cold water (290° candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and baking soda, stirring well.
Pour over popcorn and nuts in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.

title: vegetable and bacon bread ring
directions: Dip each biscuit piece in melted margarine.
Place in bottom of greased tube cake pan, making one layer.
Next, layer 1/3 of the onions, of the bell pepper, Parmesan cheese and bacon. Repeat, starting with the biscuits, until all is used, ending with the biscuits.

title: grandma ruby's impossible pie
directions: Stir all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch greased pans.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: apple-raisin stuffed pork chops
directions: Have your butcher cut pork chops to 1-inch thickness; cut a pocket on the side for stuffing.
In a bowl, combine butter, apple, stuffing mix, celery, onion, raisins, orange juice and salt.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until chops are done.

title: hush puppies with onions
directions: Combine dry ingredients, onion and egg.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Add more water if necessary.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 10 servings.

title: butter baked carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 3/4 cup water until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and save carrot liquid.
Melt the 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper and mix well.
Add carrot liquid and milk gradually.
Cook or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over carrot mixture and dot with butter.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and water in a saucepan. Bring to boil and cool.
Mix vegetables together and pour cooled liquid over vegetables.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese danish
directions: Line dish with one package of rolls.
Cream egg yolk, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Cover with second package of rolls.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer or blender until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and chop potatoes. Boil until done. Drain; salt and pepper potatoes.
Add parsley. Then add margarine and milk to cover potatoes. Set aside.

title: "veal scallopini"
directions: Dip veal in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Melt butter. Lightly brown veal on both sides.
Place veal in baking dish; set aside.
Add to can of tomato sauce and mix; sugar, oregano, basil and mint flakes.
Pour mixture over the veal.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Just before serving, put Mozzarella cheese on top, bake until cheese melts.
Right before serving, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: sangria
directions: Into a large pitcher, pour juices and sugar; stir until all dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.
Add ice just before serving.
May be doubled.

title: garden casserole
directions: Saute onion, red pepper strips and garlic in oleo until crisp-tender.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Spoon half of the onion mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer half each of the potato slices, green beans and cheese.
Repeat layers of onion mixture, potatoes and green beans.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix, oil, egg and mandarin oranges with juice.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan; pour in cake mix.
Bake 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool cake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend together cornmeal, salt and soda.
Stir in shortening. Add sour cream, corn and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in green chiles and cheeses.
Pour into a greased 9x13-inch pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk.
Add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add strawberries and pour into crust.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broth and water.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms with juice included.
Mix uncooked rice, parsley flakes, salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Pour liquid ingredients into casserole and stir.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and mix well.
Shape into balls 3/4-inch in diameter.
Add to tomato sauce and cover. Switch to high until steaming, then to low and cook for 45 minutes.
Serve with cooked spaghetti.

title: peasant girls with veils(tilslortebondepiker)
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over low heat; add the zwieback mixed with sugar and cinnamon and stir until light brown.
Allow to cool.
In a glass dessert bowl, put down a layer of zwieback followed by a layer of applesauce and a layer of whipped cream; continue for two more layers.
Serve chilled.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: german onion pie(zweibel kuchen)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute bacon until transparent.
Drain most of the fat from the pan.
Add the onions and saute until transparent.
Do not brown.
Set aside to cool.
Beat the eggs and sour cream together in a medium sized bowl.
Sprinkle the flour over the top and beat it in.
Stir in the salt and pepper.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix the pudding and milk until it just starts to thicken.
Then add the cream cheese by chunks.
Keep blending with mixer until smooth.
The mixture will still be a little lumpy which is fine.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown hamburger meat in skillet, then drain off excess fat.
Mix meat and onion; reserve a small amount and place remaining meat mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle cheese over meat; beat eggs, milk and seasoning and pour over meat and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes; reduce oven temp to 300 and bake 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle remaining meat on top and bake 5 more minutes.
Let pie stand 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add cucumbers, radishes, green peppers and carrots to the spaghetti.
Season to taste with McCormick Salad Supreme.
Pour Italian dressing over spaghetti mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Garnish with small salad tomatoes, halved or quartered.

title: san francisco chops(microwave)
directions: In a shallow dish combine oil and garlic.
Spread evenly in a dish.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Combine sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar and pepper in bowl.
Add pork chops to dish, turning over in garlic oil.
Pour sauce mixture over chops.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: donald's de-calorized gumbo
directions: Cook okra in 2 tablespoons shortening until tender and no longer slimy.
Brown flour in 4 tablespoons shortening to make a roux.
Add all ingredients to the crock-pot and let simmer about 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8. One cup yields about 150 calories.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas, add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Mix garlic powder, noodles, soy sauce, melted butter and pepper seasoning. Set aside. Mix mushroom soup, tuna, cashews and celery. Set aside. Saute onion in butter until golden brown. Add to soup mix with 1/4 c. water. Turn into shallow 4-cup casserole and top with noodle mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: olive garden alfredo pasta
directions: Melt butter; add cream, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until thick.	At the same time, cook pasta.
When alfredo has reached your desired consistency, stir in Parmesan cheese.
Drain pasta and serve with alfredo sauce.

title: fried coconut fish fillets
directions: In a shallow dish, combine coconut, crumbs and salt; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg and water together.
Dip fillets in egg mixture, then dredge through coconut mixture to coat both sides.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of oil over medium heat.
Add 2 fillets.
Fry for 4 to 6 minutes or until golden brown and fish is flaky.
Repeat with remaining oil and fish.
Serve with Lemon Butter Sauce.

title: summer waldorf salad
directions: Toss fruit and walnuts gently in large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt and honey.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fettucine all' alfredo
directions: While fettucine is cooking, cook and stir garlic
in butter in large saucepan for 1 minute.
Stir in cream; heat to boil.
Add drained fettucine and toss well.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper; toss again.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Soften gelatin over cold water for 5 minutes.
Place in microwave.
Cook 1 minute.
Sift sugar in bowl.
Whip cream until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat in gelatin mixture. Beat until stands in peaks.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: Remove core and hard veins from cabbage.
Shred and put to soak in cold water.
Saute onion in butter for a few minutes. Drain cabbage and add to butter and onion in pan.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add apples, salt and boiling water to cabbage.
Stir.
Cover and simmer gently for an hour or more.
If water is absorbed too early, add a little more.
When cabbage is tender and water is absorbed, add red wine and brown sugar. Simmer until all is incorporated and thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and salt and sift well.
Next, add the 2 sticks of butter/margarine to the dry mixture and add the eggs next.
Last, add the buttermilk and stir into flour-sugar mixture by hand.
Pour this mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This recipe will make 2 pies.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Whip instant vanilla pudding and 2 cups of milk.
Whip 2/3 of Cool Whip and sour cream to consistency you want.
Cut up bananas and mix.
Add 1/2 box of vanilla wafers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and line dish with vanilla wafers.
Crush about 6 to 8 vanilla wafers and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Preparation Time:
20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts. Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cook sugar, salt, soda and buttermilk to soft ball stage in heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk, water and add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup of mix into 2 1/2 quart bowl.
Top with 1/3 of wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layers.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Cut the crusts off of the bread.
Cover the bottom of a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer.
Add layers of Swiss cheese and ham.
Cover with rest of bread.
Mix together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over the bread, making sure all of the top layer is moistened.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil, refrigerate until 1 1/2 hours before needed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, removing foil after about 30 minutes.
It will puff up nicely and get toasty brown.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes if appearance calls for it.
This recipe can be altered with different kinds of cheese, sausage and onions, Egg Beaters and skim milk, spinach and mushrooms.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl.
Set aside.
In 1-quart bowl combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until all pieces are coated. Put on waxed paper to cool.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Use 1 cup boiling water to dissolve jello; add rest of ingredients; let set in refrigerator.

title: fruit-and-cereal brunch bread
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine egg, oil and bananas.
Add to cereal mixture. Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and next 5 ingredients.
Add to cereal mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Combine brown sugar and next 2 ingredients. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles crumbs.
Stir in pecans. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Cut sliced beef into tiny pieces.
Add to cream cheese and onion.
Spread on crackers.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9 inch pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the ingredients together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Will not be real brown on top.
Good hot or cold.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Let set.
Keep remaining jello warm. After first layer is set, layer sliced bananas and spread sour cream over top.
Add reserved jello and chill.

title: bill's homemade hot sauce
directions: Chop onion and jalapenos in a blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend to desired texture.
You can add fresh tomato if a chunkier sauce is desired.

title: travis' favorite banana bread
directions: Mix well the sugar, oil, eggs and bananas.
Sift, then add to the mixture the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Grease and flour 4 or 5 small loaf pans or 3 round coffee cans. Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems from mushroom caps. Place mushroom caps in a greased 8 X 8-inch baking dish.
Saute mushroom stems, onion and garlic in margarine for about 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients except mozzarella cheese.
Divide stuffing mixture evenly among mushroom caps.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until hot.
Top with mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese is melted (5 minutes).

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 4 to 5 hours or until tomatoes are all cooked up.

title: layered tortilla bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef in large nonstick skillet; drain well. Mix in beans, tomatoes, chiles and taco seasoning mix. Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes. Spray 9 x 13 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cut tortillas in half; place half of them in bottom of baking dish, overlapping. Spoon half of beef mixture evenly over tortillas. Cover with remaining tortillas and then remaining beef mixture. Top with cheese. Cover; bake 25 minutes. Makes 8 servings. 5.5 Weight Watcher points, 280 calories, 9 grams fat, 6 grams fiber

title: orange nut bread
directions: Combine butter, juice, rind, sugar, egg and nuts.
Mix.
Sift remaining ingredients and stir into butter mixture.
Mix well and turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: liver sausage spread
directions: Cream together liver sausage, cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Mix in onion and garlic salts.
Serve spread in a small bowl garnished with olive slices.
Serve with crackers.
