title: tangy shrimp
directions: Wrap shrimp in bacon strips and saute until bacon is done.

title: popovers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into muffin pans or popover cups.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: heavenly "death by chocolate"
directions: Bake cake as per directions.
Cool completely.
Prepare mousse as per directions.
Let set for several hours.
In a large clear bowl (I use my punch bowl), crumble half the chocolate cake, followed by half the mousse and one container of La Creme. Sprinkle with half the Nestle Crunch bar.
Repeat the layers, ending with the Crunch.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Enjoy!!

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Cover with bacon.
Cook 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, without cover, at 325°.

title: toffee popcorn crunch
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease a large roasting pan or two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Place popcorn and almonds in prepared pan. In heavy medium saucepan, combine toffee bits and corn syrup. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until toffee is melted (about 12 minutes).
Pour over popcorn mixture; stir until evenly coated.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from oven; stir 2 minutes until slightly cooled.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container in a cool, dry place.

title: hearty vegetable chowder
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Scoop out bacon with slotted spoon; drain on paper towels.
Add boiling water, onion, celery, potatoes, carrots, beans, corn, garlic powder, salt and bay leaf to bacon drippings.
Stir; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and boil slowly for about 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Blend flour and water until smooth; stir into soup.
Add pimento. Return to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Makes 2 quarts.

title: susan's refried beans
directions: Use an 8
to
10 quart heavy casserole.
Boil the beans in 6 to 8 cups water for 1 minute.
Let sit off the heat for 1 hour. Water should
cover beans as they double in size. Drain beans in a colander
and
add
fresh	water and all remaining ingredients. If you have a pressure cooker, the beans take 30 minutes to cook; otherwise keep them simmering on the stove 2 hours or until tender.
When
done,
mash	them
a
bit with a potato masher until they are thick.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and beat 6 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
In greased Bundt pan, start with batter and alternate batter and sliced apples.
Top with apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: arlene's sugar cookies
directions: Beat together oleo, eggs, sugar and lard.
Combine vanilla, baking soda and baking powder with milk.
Add flour and milk mixture alternately to sugar mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Grease and flour pan. Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla. Pour half of the batter into pan. Put apple slices on top. Add rest of batter. Top with remaining apples. Sprinkle topping of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon mixed. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice and dissolve jello.
Let cool.
Blend in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Good for several days.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep saucepan.
Bring to a simmer; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in oil, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Beat in zucchini.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon and dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Put in 2 well-greased bread pans and bake 60 to 75 minutes at 350°.

title: brendan's favorite drink
directions: Place ingredients in blender and blend.

title: swill
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on the package.
Put back on low heat.
Add soup, tuna and peas if desired.
Heat to serving temperature, stirring frequently.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars in bowl.
Beat egg in. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts. Cool. Remove skin and bones; chop. Saut onion in butter until clear. Add cream cheese, chiles and chicken. Salt and pepper to taste. Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with Pam. Fill tortillas with 2 heaping spoonfuls of chicken mixture and roll up. Place in baking dish. Continue until mixture is used. Cover enchiladas with cheese. Pour whipping cream over dish. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly (35 minutes).

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in large bowl and mix with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Spoon into 2 loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Completely cool before you put glaze on.

title: mom's cornbread dressing
directions: Place chicken in large pan and cover with water.
Boil until tender.
Add water along to have at least 1 quart of broth.
Cool chicken and remove bones.
Cool and crumble cornbread in large bowl.
Cook onion and celery in 1 tablespoon butter until onion is clear.
Add onion, celery and broth to cornbread and mix well until moist.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Beat in 3 eggs and mix well.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put part of hamburger in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add uncooked spaghetti.
Then, add 2 jars pizza sauce, rest of hamburger and more spaghetti sauce on top.
Add favorite toppings (pepperoni, mushrooms, olives, Canadian bacon, onions) to this and more Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato onion soup
directions: Bring to boil water and dip mix.
Mix instant potato flakes in water and onion mix until consistent to taste.
Serves 4.

title: coconut cream pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: *To toast, spread on baking sheet.
Place in 350° oven for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once, until light brown.

title: salad pizza
directions: Mix 1
cup water with butter in saucepan and bring to a boil. Add
flour, all at once, and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a
time, beating
well after each one.
Spread
in
ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate goo cake
directions: Mix Swiss chocolate cake mix as directed.
In bottom of large cake
pan,
sprinkle coconut and pecans.
Pour prepared cake mix on top of pecans and coconut.
Blend cream cheese and confectioners
sugar.
Dap
on
top of other mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat the soup in a saucepan and add the gelatin.
Mix well. Add the cream cheese.
When the cream cheese has melted, add the celery, green onion and shrimp.
Pour mixture into a buttered mold and chill until set.
Invert onto a serving plate and serve with crackers.

title: glazed squash with onions
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 225°.
Cook squash cut side down in water in hot skillet for 20 minutes or until just tender.
Turn squash over.
Fill each half with portion of onions and walnuts. Mix butter and corn syrup in small bowl.
Spoon over squash. Cook, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion tops and parsley for about 10 minutes on medium heat.
Add crawfish fat and cook on medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Add peeled crawfish tails and 1/2 cup of water.
Let boil for about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup of cold water and add to crawfish.
Season to taste and cook for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: beef and vegetable pie
directions: Saute onion, carrots and cabbage in hot butter in large skillet, stirring often until tender and lightly brown, about 15 minutes.
(I add some minced garlic, too.)
Put in large bowl.
In same skillet, saute meat over high heat until it loses its pink color.
Lower heat; stir in 1 cup hot water.
Stir to loosen browned bits.
Stir in cornstarch mixture, parsley, salt, savory and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes; add to the vegetables in bowl. Turn into pie crust-lined plate.
Top with second crust.
Cut slits in top.
Mix egg with 1 tablespoon water and brush over crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, until crust is nicely browned.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add banana and mix well. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add with oatmeal to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts and flavoring.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer carrots, onion and cheese.
Top with stuffing and dot with butter.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla before last flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls (about 1-inch).
Cool for an hour or two in the freezer or fridge.
Remove and dip in melted chocolate.
I use my tongs for the dipping.
Works great.
These are yummy!

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Bring cheese and butter to room temperature.
Cut rolls into quarters.
Cream cheese and butter.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Spread mix over each quarter roll.
May need to use hands to do this.
Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Bake frozen at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes or until bubbly.

title: asiago dip with crostini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl; spoon into a 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with toasted bread. Yield: 2 cups.

title: steak marinade
directions: Marinate steak for 24 hours; cook and serve.

title: blender fruit ice cream
directions: Put first four ingredients in blender and blend for 30 seconds.
Then add 2 cups frozen fruit (peaches, strawberries or blueberries) and blend for 1 minute.
Serve or freeze in blender container, until time for dessert.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until done; cool.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
In greased casserole dish, layer 2 packages broccoli, layer chicken pieces on top.
Mix the 2 cans cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise and milk.
Spread this mixture over the top of the chicken pieces; combine the shredded cheese, bread crumbs and melted butter and pour over the soup mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cookie-jar sugar cookies
directions: Roll dough to 1/8-inch thick. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: baked onions and vegetables
directions: Precook onions until tender in microwave.
Drain, cut and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Precook celery just a few seconds in microwave and add to onions.
Add tomato and squash to other vegetables.
Melt margarine in saucepan; remove from heat and mix in flour.
Gradually mix in milk. Return to medium heat and, stirring constantly, cook until it thickens (just after it comes to a boil).
Add Velveeta to cream sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until vegetables test done. Mushrooms can be added, if desired.

title: queen of all pudding
directions: Whip together. Soak 1/2 loaf bread in mixture until liquid has been absorbed. Crumble bread and place in a baking dish with remaining liquid. Spread the top with guava marmalade.
Bake at 300° until firm. May top with meringue (your favorite recipe) and brown per directions.

title: grandpa cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening. Beat in eggs, salt, soda, baking powder and vanilla. Mix in flour well. Add oatmeal and coconut.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Press flat with fork dipped in cold water. Bake in preheated 375° oven about 7 minutes (until light golden brown).
Cool on rack. Store in airtight container in freezer.
(One pound coffee cans are good containers.)

title: special sweet potato casserole
directions: In bowl, mix sweet potatoes, 1/2 cup butter and granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Pour into baking dish.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix raisins, soda, butter and boiling water.
Soak for 4 to 5 hours.
Add flour, sugar, cinnamon and eggs.
Stir and mix well. Put in 6 well-greased and floured tin cans (number 303 size). Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and set aside.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
In a large bowl, mix broth, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Add cooked spaghetti, onion mixture, chicken and 1/2 of cubed Velveeta cheese; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; top with remaining cheese.
Cook about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper and onion.
Drain fat.
Add tomato soup.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add chicken soup to noodles. Layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture in large casserole with cheese between layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: apple cider salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot cider; add cold cider, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until partly set.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Put into 6-cup mold.
Chill overnight.
Serve with mayonnaise.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
In mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Beat with mixer until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes (9-inch pans for 40 minutes).

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients very thoroughly. Once ingredients are thoroughly mixed, put in a decorative dish and place pineapple slices and cherries on top.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, lemon extract and apricot nectar in large bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour mixture in pan and bake according to directions on box.
Cool 15 minutes in pan. Remove and glaze with powdered sugar and lemon juice.

title: stuffed eggplant rolls
directions: Skin eggplant and cut lengthwise slices about 1/8-inch thick. Dip slices in egg batter and then in bread crumbs.
Fry and cool slices in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Place a slice of Prosciutto on each slice of eggplant.
Chop hard-boiled eggs.
Mix in grated cheese and place on top of Prosciutto.
Add grated Mozzarella on top of this, then roll each slice and secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Pour sauce and Mozzarella on top. Bake until cheese is all melted at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southern chicken pie
directions: In saucepan, brown sausage and drain on paper towel.
Pour out fat.
In same pan, melt oleo.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened. Cook 1 minute more.
Add remaining; heat through.
Top with Savory Pastry.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients.
Add beef.
Stir in rice and cheese.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: in a hurry rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour into dry ingredients with melted shortening and egg. Mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Fill half full. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in oleo.
Set aside. Save out 1 cup of mixture and mix with coconut.
Set aside.
Peel and slice apples and mix with cornstarch, 1/3 cup sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well and cook over medium heat for 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and oleo; mix well.

title: salmon ball
directions: Blend all ingredients but parsley and nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper to form ball.
(It will be quite soft.) Refrigerate overnight.
Remove and roll in parsley and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: easy quiche
directions: Place bread slices on bottom of baking dish. Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over bread.
Brown sausage and pour over bread.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight and bake in the morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add to all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crock-pot ham
directions: Place ham in crock-pot. Mix pineapple with juice, brown sugar and cola. Pour over ham. Cover and cook until hot.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and sour cream.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in.
Pour batter into Bundt pan. Sprinkle with a topping of 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Dot with extra.

title: green chili-cheese quiche
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to
30 minutes.
May be halved for a small group.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corned beef ball
directions: In mixing bowl, thin cream cheese with horseradish sauce, blending well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball and refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add minced fresh mint to new peas.
While cooking or just before serving, add a tablespoon or two of green mint jelly to the cooked peas with salt and pepper.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, lard and eggs together, then add the flour and sour milk alternately.
Last add the boiling water, soda, vanilla and salt.
Cake stays moist until gone.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: With hands, mix all ingredients. Roll into balls. Freeze. Bake while still frozen at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes- until brown. Yields about 8 dozen.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, cornmeal and salt all together.
Mix together melted margarine, butter and cocoa.
Add to the first mixture, then add vanilla and whipping cream.
Pour into the 10-inch pricked with fork 3 times in middle pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Fill 9-inch cake pan 2/3 full of sliced apples.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Mix 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons flour, 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup melted margarine and 1 egg.
Spread this mixture over apples and sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: miss martha's gonic tonic
directions: Mix juices and sherbets in a punch bowl; carefully stir in the birch beer.
Serve immediately.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers together.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Add rice (medium heat ). Simmer for a few minutes until all ingredients are warm.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box, except use only 2 cups of milk.
After the pudding is thick, add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Mix together gently.
Layer with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: shrimp stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown onions and celery (if use beef, brown it also) in shortening.
Add rice, chopped shrimp, egg, cheese, Italian seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff peppers firmly with stuffing.
Place in a 5-quart heavy boiler with tomato sauce, Ragu and sugar.
Add approximately 2 cups water.
Sprinkle peppers with paprika.
Boil on medium heat for about 1 hour with pot covered.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs.
Cook sauce and meatballs all day in crock-pot.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Rinse, drain and sort through beans, discarding any that float.
Melt margarine in Dutch oven or large skillet.
Saute onion, garlic, parsley and green pepper in margarine.
Add beans, 8 cups water, ham seasoning, sausage, green onions, bay leaves, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Boil gently, stirring occasionally, for about 1 1/2 hours, or until tender. Add additional water while cooking, if necessary.
(Mash a few beans on side of pot to make beans creamy, if desired.)
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Serve on hot, cooked rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in casserole dish.
Add Cheez Whiz (this can be done in microwave).
Add Veg-All and mix together. Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add Ritz crackers.
Put this mixture on top of casserole and brown in oven or place in microwave until bubbly.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Sift together the flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cook butter and sugar over low heat, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted ingredients and nuts; mix well (the batter will be quite stiff).
Spread in greased pan. Bake in preheated oven (350°) for about 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil, salt and pepper in deep skillet or wok.
Add cabbage, celery, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and sugar.
Stir in chicken broth; cook about 10 minutes.

title: fancy franks
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with toothpicks.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Stir until moistened. Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove from pan, cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: blanc mange(filling for cream puffs or pies)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Heat milk on medium heat until warm, but not boiling.
Remove 1/2 cup of heated milk and add to flour, sugar and salt mixture.
Add the beaten egg yolks and stir well.
Allow the remaining milk to come to a boil, then gradually stir in egg mixture, stirring constantly or it will lump.
As soon as it has thickened and started boiling, immediately take off heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pitcher. Stir well.
Serve over ice.
Makes 9 cups.

title: apple pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugars, flour and spices; set aside. In a large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice. Add sugar mixture; toss well to coat. Line a 9-inch pie pan with half the pastry. Place apple filling into crust; dot with butter. Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie. Cut a few slits in top of pie. Beat egg white until foamy; brush over pastry. Sprinkle sugar on top. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Increase temperature to 400° and bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until golden. Yield: 8 servings.

title: fresh asparagus soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add asparagus and paprika; cook until asparagus turns bright green.
Stir in chicken broth and cream. Heat to boiling.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into soup. Cook until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: lemon or orange chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and coriander with wire whisk and set aside. Preheat oven to 300°.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar with electric mixer at medium speed to form a grainy paste.
Add eggs and extract and beat.
Scrape sides of bowl.
With mixer at low speed, combine with flour mixture.
When all ingredients are blended, add chocolate chips.
Do not overmix.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart; they'll spread.
Bake 15 minutes on center rack of oven.
Do not brown! Immediately transfer to cooling racks.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: egg-a-la-goldenrod
directions: Slip the yolks out of the whites.
Mash yolks with fork.
Chop the whites.
Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour and cook over low heat until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add seasoning.
Blend chopped egg whites into cream sauce.
Pour over toast.
Top with egg yolks.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in two unbaked pie shells 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together. Transfer to a slow cooker. Cover and cook on high until heated through. Stir occasionally. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
In a medium bowl, combine salmon, cream cheese, onion, lemon juice, liquid smoke, horseradish and salt.
Wrap in wax paper to form a ball.
Chill until firm.
Roll in parsley and pecans.
Chill until ready to use.
Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: old-fashioned caramel cake
directions: Combine sour cream and milk; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 round 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla and almond extracts in a large mixer bowl until fluffy.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 5 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool layers 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely. Fill and frost layers with Caramel Frosting.

title: carrot casserole surprise
directions: Cook and mash carrots.
Beat in sugar, flour, margarine and baking powder, then blend in milk.
Beat eggs until light.
Fold into carrot mixture; blend in cinnamon.
Turn into greased 6 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Serves 6.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water; beat for about 7 minutes, stopping a few times to clean beater and sides of boiler with scraper.
Remove from boiling water when frosting stands in glossy peaks (has more body than meringue).
Continue beating until frosting is cool and thick enough to form swirls.
This is enough for 3 layers or 1 pound cake.

title: sour cream coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar until very creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, baking powder and soda; mix well.
Add sour cream and flavorings, then coconut.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook the chuck roast until tender; shred into small pieces. Combine the remaining ingredients. Boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add beef and simmer for 1/2 hour in covered pan. Serve on buns.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Chip up and saute garlic cloves and onion in 1 1/2 tbsp. olive oil.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and season.
Saute diced onion and green pepper in butter.
Cook Creamettes; drain.
Layer in casserole dish the Creamettes noodles, meat, pepper and onion, spoonfuls of celery soup and cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll into balls and flatten out with (crystal) bottom, greased and sugared.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: basic cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers.
Soften bread crumbs with chicken broth.
Add sauteed vegetables and eggs.
Stir your dressing until it is smooth.
There is no way to tell if this has the right amount of salt unless you taste it.
You can vary this by adding 1/8 teaspoon Mexican chili powder or Creole seasoning gives it a good flavor.
Chopped parsley is always good.
Heat in 400° oven until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add ground meat.
Cook, breaking up the meat until meat loses its pink color.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Stir and whip sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk. Put in casserole dish.
Then mix brown sugar, nuts, flour and butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss chicken
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, lay chicken breasts.
Cover chicken with Swiss cheese.
Warm soup and add wine.
Pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
During last 1/2 hour, top with crumbs.

title: aunt lee's hopscotchers
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt the morsels and peanut butter, stir constantly.
When melted, remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and potato sticks and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and butter; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat condensed milk, flour, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa, egg, vanilla and baking powder. Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over crust; top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: one pan potatoes and chicken rosemary
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick and microwave 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
While potatoes cook, in large skillet, toss and brown chicken and garlic in oil over high heat 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and rosemary; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: paul's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well for at least 1 hour.
Add together 3/4 stick of margarine with cheese; melt in saucepan.
Add broccoli; stir well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Chop or grind crackers; mix together with 1/4 stick of melted margarine. Spoon on top of broccoli.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a 3-quart greased casserole, place 6 tortillas.
Brown hamburger with seasoning, place on tortillas.
Spread beans, then 6 tortillas; layer in order the Velveeta, soup and tomatoes.
Cook at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
This dish freezes well.

title: dani's unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Heat sugar, cocoa, milk, and oleo in saucepan until bubbling well. Cook for 3 minutes, then add vanilla. Pour mixture over oats and nuts. Drop by tsp. on waxed paper.
Cool.
* A variation is to omit the cocoa and 1 c. of oats, substituting: 1 c. of peanut butter and 20 miniature marshmallows.

title: frosted apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour a 13x9-inch baking pan. Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl. Add applesauce, oil, vanilla and eggs. Beat at low speed until moistened. Then beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Fold in 1/2 cup walnuts. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until done. Cool in pan. Makes 16 servings.

title: dora allin's scalloped eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until soft, drain.
Add butter, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Beat the eggs into the milk and add to eggplant. Add cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until it is firm throughout, about 45 to 50 minutes.
During final 10 to 15 minutes, add remaining cheese to melt on top.

title: english pizza muffins
directions: Spread on English muffins.
Broil until bubbles.

title: fruit muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups or lightly grease bottoms only with nonstick cooking spray. Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add combined milk, oil and egg whites; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in fruit.
Fill prepared muffin cups almost full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or store tightly wrapped in freezer.
To reheat, microwave on High about 30 seconds per muffin.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Mix well.
Simmer until good and hot.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in small bowl; set aside. Combine eggs, oil and water; mix well.
Wash mushrooms.
Dredge mushrooms in flour mixture and dip in egg mixture.
Roll in breadcrumbs.
Chill 1 1/2 hours.
Deep-fry mushrooms in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Yields 32 appetizers. Serve with tartar sauce.

title: *lazy spinach pispalita(romanian quiche)
directions: In a medium bowl, place thawed and squeezed dry spinach, butter, cottage cheese and Feta cheese. Mix together and set aside.

title: crabmeat melts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on English muffins. Freeze.
Bake frozen English muffins at 375° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Broil last 2 to 3 minutes until crispy.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Combine baking soda and water and add to mixture.
Mix.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Season with lemon juice, salt, pepper, celery salt and paprika.
Place in crock-pot.
In a medium bowl or pan, mix mushroom and celery soups with sherry. Pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve chicken and sauce over hot fluffy rice.
Makes 8 to 12 servings (about 3 quarts).

title: small strawberry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and butter together. Put 1/2 in bottom of pan. Mix Dream Whip as directed. Beat sugar and cream cheese together. Mix Dream Whip with cream cheese mixture. Put half on crumbs. Put strawberries on top of cream cheese mixture. Put strawberry glaze on strawberries. Then put other half of cream cheese on strawberry glaze. Add other half of crumbs.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: You may add shredded cheese, if you wish.

title: grace's pickles
directions: Add salt and ice cubes to cucumbers.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric together.
Bring to boil, add cucumbers.
Bring to boil once more and put in pint jars and seal.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: pear sauce
directions: Put the pears in the blender; blend it up.
Shake in as much cinnamon and nutmeg as you want.
Serve with pork chops or on top of cottage cheese.

title: spanish style white rice
directions: Place a medium size pan on stove top with medium flame.
Pour the salt and oil and let simmer for a minute.
Pour in the water. Let water start to boil.
While that is beginning to boil, pour rice in a bowl and wash the rice.
When the water is boiling, pour the rice in.
Let the water dry up.
When this has happened, stir the rice around and bring the flame down.

title: elizabeth fendley's spinach con queso
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze until dry.
In a microwavable bowl, combine cheese (cut into cubes), mushrooms, spinach, tomatoes, cilantro and peppers.
Microwave 3 minutes on High and stir. Repeat until cheese is melted.
Add milk and microwave 2 minutes on Medium-high.
Serve with warm flour tortillas (tear in half, roll and dip).

title: tea drink
directions: Soak tea bags overnight.
Add sugar, lemon juice extract and ginger ale.
Add enough water to make a gallon (about 2 quarts plus 1 cup water).

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° until done.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: In large pan, cook onion and garlic in oil.
Add pasta sauce; simmer 15 minutes.
In bowl, mix ricotta, spinach, 1 cup mozzarella, parmesan and eggs.
In 15 by 9-inch baking dish, layer sauce, lasagna and cheeses accordingly.
Reserve half of mozzarella.
Cover and bake at 350 for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining mozzarella.
Bake 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a small bowl, combine lime juice, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Add chicken; stir.
Marinate for 15 minutes.
In a nonstick skillet, cook onion, chicken and marinade for 3 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add peppers; saute for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in salsa.
Divide mixture among tortillas; top with cheese and sour cream.
Roll up and serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix in flour to stiff; enough to roll out. Roll out thin and bake at 350°.

title: stuffed french toast(with warmed maple syrup and pecans)
directions: Cut French bread in cubes.
Butter a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Place half of bread cubes in pan.
Top with cream cheese cubes.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over bread.
Press down.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with warm syrup and butter.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Combine sugar, water, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice; chill. When ready to serve, add ginger ale and peppermint extract.
Makes 36 1/2 cup servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture in thirds, alternating with milk.
Turn into 10-inch tube cake pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: plain layer cake
directions: Cream the shortening with half the sugar; add the remaining sugar gradually with the beaten eggs.
Next, add the milk and flavoring.
Then add the dry ingredients, sifted together.
Beat thoroughly and bake in prepared layer cake
pans for 15 to 20 minutes in a moderately hot oven at 400°.

title: belgian shrimp
directions: Mince very fine the shallots, garlic, chives or onion slice or put through the finest blade of a meat grinder; add thyme, parsley and tarragon and mix well.
Add to butter, blending well.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except shrimp), folding in the bread crumbs last of all.
This makes a rather stiff paste.
It can be used at once or stored in a covered jar in the refrigerator.
Divide the shrimp into 4 piles.
Spread layer of the mixture 1/4-inch thick over the bottoms of 4 pottery baking dishes or individual casserole dishes.
Place a covering layer of shrimp in spoon fashion in rows on top, pressing the shrimp into the mixture.
Use the remaining mixture to cover the shrimp.
Place the dishes in a 400° oven and cook for 10 minutes, then broil until tops are brown.
Serve at once.

title: deluxe nachos
directions: Spread beans over tortilla chips.
Heat dip according to package directions.
Spoon over tortilla chips.
Top with tomato, olives and onions.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Melt butter and stir in mustard.
Coat chicken pieces with mixture.
Combine crumbs and pepper.
Dip chicken into bread crumbs and place in shallow baking pan.
Do not overlap chicken. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves about 4.
You can double.

title: portuguese sausage and lentil soup
directions: Cook sausage whole.
Cool, slice and reserve.
In heavy soup pot, saute ham, onion, pepper and carrot in oil until tender. Stir in seasoning.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Add all other ingredients except last two.
Cover pot partially and simmer gently for 2 hours.
Taste; adjust seasoning with salt and pepper. Add shredded spinach and serve.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (325°) 2 hours, stirring several times during baking.
The mixture should not boil.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: sissy's upside down pizza
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion together. Brown meat and onion until the meat crumbles. Stir in tomato sauce. Add spaghetti and the spaghetti sauce mix. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Spoon this mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with sour cream and sprinkle with the cheese. Unroll the crescent rolls and place on top of cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until top is golden brown. Let cool and slice.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients at low speed until moistened. Beat for 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (test for doneness with toothpick).
Poke large holes in top of hot cake 1 to 1 1/2 inches apart.
Combine Eagle Brand and caramel topping and pour slowly and evenly over top of cake.
Refrigerate to cool.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: gingered chicken(microwave needed)
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, with the thickest parts to the outside edge of the 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients (except cornstarch and water) and pour over chicken.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High (100%) for 10 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken, rotating dish 1/2 turn. Cover and microwave until thickest parts of chicken are done, 7 to 10 minutes longer.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine ingredients; roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: kathy's beef and potato casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Alternate layers of sliced potatoes and onions.
Add can of canned beef and stock, crumpled up.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cream celery soup, mixed together.
Pour over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake about 1 hour at 325° to 350° or until tender.
Remove foil.
Turn oven up higher and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Return beef to skillet.
Add onion, celery, mushrooms, soup and garlic salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat over low heat to serving temperature.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients really well.
Put in 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: beef italians(casserole)
directions: Crumble beef in microwave tray.
Add onion and green pepper. Microwave at High 3 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave uncovered at High 9 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand until cheese melts.

title: never-fail rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast together and let set 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salt, sugar and 1 cup of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and oleo.
Mix, then add remaining flour.
Mix well.
Let rise until double.
Roll in any shape.
Place in well-greased pan.
Let rise about 1 hour, or until double.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: gramma maries' molasses cookies
directions: Makes 5 dozen soft, sugar-coated cookies.
Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and molasses.
In another bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
This dough should be very soft, yet roll into a ball.
If it's humid, it takes more flour.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese. Add pineapple. Add Cool Whip. Fold in oranges. Keep chilled.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Combine the 1 cup flour and confectioners sugar.
Melt butter and add, stirring, until well mixed. Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: rodeo stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown ground chuck partially.
Add onions and continue browning.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.
Yields 8 servings.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle veggies on top.
Roll tortillas, then slice into 2-inch pieces.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar of artichokes into frying pan; drain the other jar (save for other uses).
Chop all the artichokes; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to pan; saute until limp.
Beat eggs in a bowl; add crumbs, salt, oregano and hot pepper.
Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes and onion mixture.
Turn into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan; bake at 325° for about 30 minutes until set.
Let cool in pan; cut into squares.
Serve cold or heat in 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 1-inch squares.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake.

title: italian cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes, then bake at 250° for 50 minutes or until very firm.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with skins on.
Peel and put in casserole. Cover with sauce.
Combine all ingredients but butter and nuts. Cook until thick.
Add butter and nuts, pour over potatoes so all are glazed.
Bake, covered, 25 minutes at 375°.

title: susie's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate overnight.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Mix the pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and eggs in double boiler and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Whip the cream and fold into cool custard mixture.
Add almonds, cherries, apple and celery.
Freeze in freezer tray or molds.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: canned hot peppers
directions: Thoroughly wash peppers, cut in two, remove seeds and pack into clean jars.
Add water.
Fill with vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt (pint jars).
Do not process.
Heat lids and seal.
Don't be alarmed if jars do not seal.
They will keep.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot taco sauce
directions: Delicious served as dip with tortilla chips.
Mix together and serve chilled.

title: flan(cuban dessert)
directions: Take 4 tablespoons of sugar with a few drops of water and heat in loaf pan until dark brown or almost burnt.
Mix ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Place pan in another baking dish with water covering the bottom of the pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine and bake in casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Mix bacon, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spoon on bread.
Bake until cheese is bubbly.
Serves 20.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Roll in chopped pecans. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Preheat cooking oil in medium size frying pan.
Layer the following ingredients in the following order:
one chicken breast, one slice of ham and a half slice of Swiss cheese.
Roll the layered ingredients.
Use toothpicks to assure your roll is secure. Repeat until all chicken breasts are in a roll.
You should have 6 different rolls.
Dip the rolled chicken in the beaten eggs and then roll in the bread crumbs.
Once breaded, cook in cooking oil until browned.
Serve hot with a wine sauce poured over the top.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat; blend in flour.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Add water, bay leaf, salt, red pepper and parsley. Boil until mixture is consistency of thick soup.
Fold in crab meat; put in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: orange buttermilk meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
With a wire whisk gradually blend in orange juice, the buttermilk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in orange peel.
Remove pan from heat and set aside.
Prepare 3 egg white meringue. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Cool on a wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to the zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and put into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked ham
directions: Put ham in shallow pan.
Score top of ham.
Place whole cloves in cross sections.
Pour 1 can Pepsi over ham; sprinkle on brown sugar.
Bake in slow oven until tender, basting often.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar together until grainy.
Add peanut butter and work until it turns brown.
Add 3 cups Rice Krispies and shape into balls.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in microwave for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix with sausage in a bowl using your hand.
Add 1 cup Bisquick.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When ready to serve, bake in oven at 375°
for about 15 minutes.
Turn the balls over and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: my favorite christmas salad my mother made
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise and blend until smooth. Fold in whipped cream, fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 1-quart refrigerator tray.
Freeze until firm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: vidalia deep dish
directions: Cook rice in water for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Peel and chop onions.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat; add onion and cook for 15 minutes stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in rice and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: mary's fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit, coconut and nuts.
Stir in eggs.
Add part of flour and
stir
to
coat.
Add spices and baking powder to the remaining
flour.
Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add other liquids and blend thoroughly.
Add flour and mix well.
Combine creamed mixture with fruit mixture. Bake in 2 greased tube pans at 250° for 2
to 3 hours.
Wrap cakes tightly and allow to mellow for a couple of weeks before serving.

title: miss oklahoma cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and add chocolate chips. Pour in greased and floured Bundt cake pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, then at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese rugalach
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Knead with hands until there is even consistency.
Form into large loaf, similar to Italian or French bread.
Wrap in waxed paper (refrigerate overnight).

title: jerry's strawberry pie
directions: Mix in saucepan sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water and cook until clear.
Add lemon
juice and a few drops red food coloring.
Wash and drain strawberries.
Put filling in cooled crust, then strawberries and repeat until all is used.
Cool until firm.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Gently remove the shell from the hard-boiled eggs and cut in 1/2. Place cut side down in a baking dish greased with margarine. In a saucepan, melt the margarine; add the flour and cook, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes. Add the half and half gradually and stir until mixture thickens and season with House Seasoning. Add the dry mustard and the Gruyere and stir until melted. Pour the sauce over the eggs and sprinkle top with Parmesan. Bake for approximately 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbling and top is golden brown.

title: low calorie onion dip
directions: Blend yogurt and cottage cheese in medium bowl. Stir in onion soup mix and chili powder. Refrigerate, covered, for 3 hours. Serve with an assortment of crisp vegetables and chilled boiled shrimp.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pot, brown turkey and onions.
Drain all of juices except tomatoes and add all ingredients except cheese and chips to turkey mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve with tortilla chips.
You might add chopped onions, also.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain and season.
In separate pan, melt butter.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour sauce over potatoes and mix.
For creamed potatoes, omit cheese.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in chicken broth; add water to cover potatoes. Cook until tender.
Cook celery, onions and carrots in butter in skillet until tender.
Add to potatoes; add enough milk to taste. Add salt and pepper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° in unbaked pie shell.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Spray frying pan with Pam.
Brown onion and garlic.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Brown 4 chicken breasts.
Pour 1/2 can spaghetti sauce in a crock-pot.
Add chicken and seasonings.
Pour remaining sauce in crock-pot and cook all day on low.

title: milky way cake(family recipe)
directions: Put candy bars in large pan and melt with margarine, stirring until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Remove from fire and add sugar, cooling slightly.
In bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking soda.
Put Milky Way mixture in large mixing bowl. Alternately add flour and buttermilk until all is used.
Add pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan that the bottom has been lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until test for done.

title: ham dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: hot and spicy potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato into 4 wedges.
Soak wedges (with skins left on) in salt water for 2 hours.
Mix flour, pepper, garlic and barbecue seasoning.
Roll potato wedges in flour mixture and deep fry until browned.

title: sugar syrup
directions: Brown sugar in iron skillet, stirring all of the time to prevent scorching.
When brown, mix with boiling water and cook to a syrup.

title: green bean cheesy
directions: Cook green beans by themselves for about 15 minutes (salt if desired).
Melt butter; gradually add 1 tablespoon of flour at a time.
Add milk.
Cook until you get a smooth sauce, then add chili powder, cheese (grated) and soup.
Cook until all is melted.
Add green beans.

title: hawaiian cheese spread
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Use on favorite crackers or as a dip.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken on lightly greased 13x9x2 in. dish. Add vegetables; mix broth and soup and pour over ingredients in dish.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 32 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: secrets from the sea
directions: Add cheese to white sauce.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.

title: green salad and dressing
directions: Cut cabbage and broccoli. Add raisins and almonds.
Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Add to vegetables and mix.

title: 24-hour vegetable salad
directions: Top layer of mayonnaise seals in crispness.

title: three bean and beef ranchero
directions: Brown ground beef, then combine all the ingredients, except grated cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add grated cheese and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Drain grease from sausage.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan generously.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato paste, oregano, water and salt.
Transfer this into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top with onions, peppers, tomatoes, mushrooms and cheese.
Beat together the remaining 4 ingredients until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter breakfast muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until blended well.
In separate bowl sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
In a separate bowl, mix milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients, alternating with milk and peanut butter mixture.
Blend well.
Use #24 scoop and portion into cupcake liners.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix together
flour,
sugar,
baking powder, salt and unbeaten egg with fork
until
crumbly
and sprinkle over the apples.
Pour melted
margarine
over crumb mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake
to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with cream, ice cream or
white	sweet
sauce.
Try
on trusting husband. Serves 8.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a heavy skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce. Remove from heat.
Boil noodles in salted water for 10 minutes. Drain.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook beef in 2 teaspoons oil or butter until it is browned. Pour off grease.
Add cream cheese, onion, garlic and salt.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add ground beef and add tomato sauce.
Add broccoli; pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil, extending over edge.
Grease foil.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir into chocolate the sugar until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts until well blended.
Spread into prepared pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat just until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with beans and cole slaw.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter and then in crumb mixture.
Arrange pieces in single layer in large shallow dish.
Pour remaining margarine over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: In large kettle, place ribs, onion quarters, salt and pepper sauce in 3 quarts water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours until very tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, make barbecue sauce in medium saucepan.
Combine all ingredients for sauce and simmer, uncovered, for one hour, stirring occasionally. Arrange ribs on rack in broiler pan, basting frequently with sauce 10 minutes on each side.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Mix and serve.
Add slices of fresh fruit, if desired.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms. Combine soup, sherry and sour cream.
Pour over chicken, covering it completely.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs and jam.
Add soda to milk and stir.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and spices and beat thoroughly.
Bake in loaf or layers at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cool to lukewarm.
Add flour and all other ingredients; stir well.
Form into ball with greased hands.
Store in large greased bowl covered in refrigerator until needed.
Make into rolls; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in 400° oven until lightly browned.
Brush with butter.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and beat well. Add sour milk, salt, cinnamon and flour. Mix well. Blend in jam by hand. Pour into pans and bake at 350°. Can ice with Seven Minute Frosting.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Mix (Jimmy Dean) sausage, onion flakes, Ro-Tel and salt together in a pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sausage is done.
Add flour and 1 cup milk and stir until lumps are gone. Add the remaining 2 cups milk and stir frequently until gravy thickens.
Serve over hot biscuits.
Yields 4 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat the egg, then add milk and oil.
Blend in the dry ingredients and stir until just moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Gently fold in the blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar together until dissolved. Add oil and flour and knead about 5 minutes.
Place in an oiled bowl and cover.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Punch down and form in well oiled pizza pan.

title: grandmother's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Stir butter to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream together until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 round paper-lined pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in large bowl; stir well. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish; spread out evenly. Bake for 40 minutes or until top is golden brown and bubbly.

title: darlene's meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl mix hamburger, egg, soup mix, and cracker meal. Shape into 1 in. meatballs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with pet milk.
Put meatballs in a large sauce pan and pour soup mixture over the top. Add kitchen bouquet for color.
Simmer for 20 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk and peppers.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly. Serve with tostado chips. May be kept warm in a fondue pot.

title: oven fried orange roughy(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray baking dish with vegetable oil spray.
In shallow bowl or pie plate combine the milk and salt. Add the fillets and coat them well.
In second shallow bowl or pie plate combine the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and thyme.
Remove fillets one at a time from the milk and dip them into the crumb mixture, coating them thoroughly.
Place the breaded fillets in a prepared baking dish.
Place pan in middle of the oven and bake fillets 12 minutes or until they are just baked through.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, add milk, salt and mustard.
Put bread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sausage, then cheese. Top with egg mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together in microwave oven.
Mix together the flour, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Blend with the melted butter and peanut butter.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over meat in a large size Reynolds cooking bag.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until very tender.
Pour everything in bag over sliced roast when finished.
Serve with cooked noodles and tossed salad.
Serves 6. Enjoy!

title: dora's meat loaf
directions: Chop bread in food processor.
Add seasonings.
Add to meat. Chop onion.
Add tomatoes, eggs and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix together; add all to meat and mix well.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add pineapple.
Add, sifted together, flour, baking soda and salt.
Bake in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch or 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Drop on cooking pan (or you may roll out and cut).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: georgia cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole dish. Mix flour, sugar and milk into dish.
Heat peaches in own juice and add to casserole.
Do not stir. Bake until golden brown.

title: veal gypsy goulash
directions: Cut veal in 1-inch cubes.
Dredge meat in flour, pressing in as much as possible.
Add meat to hot oil.
Add salt and paprika. Stir meat until thoroughly browned, then add hot water, onion, garlic and bay leaf.
Cover pot with lid and cook slowly until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper and cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on double layers of bread.
Let rest 1/2 hour.
Bake in 350° oven until puffed and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Line pan with dried beef.
Top with 6 to 8 boneless chicken breasts.
Lay 1/2 strip of bacon over each piece.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 3 hours at 250°.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Drop small teaspoon size balls into powdered sugar.
Place cookies on greased or sprayed cookie sheet and flatten a little.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix mashed bananas with fork.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's jelly roll
directions: Sift flour once, then measure.
Add baking powder and sift three times.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold in sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Add water and vanilla, then mix in flour lightly.
Line a jelly roll pan or shallow pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch, with aluminum foil, then grease with shortening.
Bake in medium oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Generously sprinkle powdered sugar on a dry towel a little larger than the cake.
Turn out the cake on towel, and while hot carefully roll cake and towel from narrow end.
Let cool on wire rack about 30 minutes, then unroll cake and spread jelly on the cake.
Roll up again without the towel.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and heat until bubbly.

title: bonnie's blueberry muffins
directions: *If using frozen blueberries, rinse and pat dry before adding to batter.

title: milk gravy
directions: Cook your meat.
Then remove your meat and reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Heat and add flour.
Stir continually until just begins to brown.
Gradually add milk and water.
Continue to stir. Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until desired thickness.

title: oven fried turkey
directions: Cut raw turkey breast into serving size pieces.
Wash thoroughly.
Beat egg and stir in soy sauce.
Dip turkey in mixture, then coat with cornflake crumbs.
Bake in foil-lined shallow baking pan at 350°.
Test for doneness after 45 minutes. Serve with additional soy sauce.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into glass pie pan or baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°.
Serve hot or cold, with crackers or garlic bread.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: To one quart home-canned tomatoes, add salt and pepper to taste, butter and sugar.
Mix and let come to boil.

title: taco pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake pie crust according to package directions, but cut baking time in half.
In a large heavy skillet, over medium-high heat, cook ground beef until evenly brown; drain excess fat.

Divide beans evenly into each pie shell, smearing over the bottoms and sides of partially baked shells. Spread a layer of ground beef over the beans, and top with the onion, crushed tortilla chips, and cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown, and the cheese is bubbly.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and black olives.

title: funny face pizza
directions: Decorate pizza with vegetables as follows: steamed broccoli floret or grated carrots for hair and eyebrows, small mushroom for nose and olives for eyes, pepper for mouth and zucchini for cheeks.
Or use different vegetables and your imagination.
Cook pizza according to directions.

title: warm crabmeat dip(party sized)
directions: Combine in top of double boiler the cream cheese, mustard, Miracle Whip, confectioners sugar and onion.
Stir until hot and well blended.
Do not boil.
(I put it in microwave.) Then add, with a folding motion, crabmeat and white wine.
Pour into chafing dish.
Serve warm with crackers as a dip.

title: cranberry sorbet
directions: Process in blender until sugar dissolves.
Place in metal bowl and freeze until almost firm.
Return to blender and blend again. Freeze until solid.
Makes 3 cups.

title: green beans and noodles(low-fat)
directions: Drain green beans and cook noodles as directed.
Mix the beans, noodles and dressing together and heat in a medium saucepan on the stove.

title: baked chicken breast and vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave (no water) for 4 to 5 minutes. Brown chicken breast in a very small amount of oil.
Chicken should be lightly battered in flour with salt and pepper. Dissolve 1 chicken bouillon cube in 1/4 cup water.
Pour over vegetables after cooking in microwave.
Top vegetables with browned breast.
Cook covered at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pesto with pasta
directions: Pesto:

Combine the basil, garlic and nuts in the bowl of a food processor and chop. Leave the motor running and add the olive oil in a slow, steady stream. Shut off water; add the cheeses, pinch of salt and pepper to taste. Process briefly to combine ingredients.

title: olivier salad
directions: Boil potatoes and carrots in skin (it helps to keep the vitamins). Let them cool and then peel them. Boil eggs and meat. Chop potatoes, carrots, eggs, meat and dill pickles into 1/2-inch squares. Add green peas and salt. Trust your own taste, everything must be in proportion. Stir mayonnaise only for the part of salad you are going to eat. It will keep better without it. Mix the salad and refrigerate for a while. If you want your salad a little tender, mix a part of mayonnaise with an equal part of sour cream. Bon appetit ! ! !

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place meat in bottom of casserole. Add remaining ingredients. Top with can of soup and water. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: monkey salad(sounds yucky, but tastes great!)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. In another bowl, mix the broccoli, raisins, peanuts and scallions together and refrigerate overnight.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble up. Toss all together 4 hours before serving and enjoy.

title: skillet green peppers
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat olive oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes and croutons.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until peppers are crisply tender (6 to 8 minutes).
Add tomatoes.
Continue cooking 1 minute.
Sprinkle with croutons; serve immediately.
Makes 5 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until bouillon granules dissolve.
Set BBQ sauce aside.
Combine beef and next 5 ingredients, blend. Shape mixture into small loaves (makes about 6-8).
Place on lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 in baking dish.
Spoon sauce over loaves.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans twice.
Discard any that look bad.
Put in a 3-quart or bigger heavy pot.
Add water, ham and sausage.
Cook, uncovered, on medium heat.
While beans are soaking, chop and add scallions, pepper, celery and onions.
Then add thyme and bay leaves.
When mixture boils, reduce heat and cover; cook for 3 hours, stirring every 20 to 30 minutes.
Then, with wooden spoon, mash about 1/4 of the beans.
If they don't mash up easily, continue cooking for another 1/2 hour.
About 30 minutes before serving, season with a drop or two of Tabasco sauce.
Don't use too much.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: "chamela" italian cookies(great for dunking, fill you up for hours!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Cream butter. Add sugar and beat until mixed.
Mix in eggs and lemon flavoring. In a separate bowl, stir flour and baking powder together. Add flour mixture to butter mixture.
Note: If batter is too dry to mix, add a bit of milk.
Use hands to shape pieces of dough into a loop shape (or modified pretzel shape). Place on cookie sheets and bake 8 to 10 minutes or longer if bottoms are not browned.

title: creamy green onion spread
directions: In a small bowl beat cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Stir in onions.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sauteed cherry tomatoes
directions: With a small sharp knife, cut a small cross in the stem end of each tomato.
Put the tomatoes in a single layer in a medium size saucepan.
Add the oil and garlic and sprinkle with the salt. Saute over low heat until tomatoes are just heated through, about 5 minutes, stirring gently several times.
Sprinkle with the parsley and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: oven beef stew
directions: In 3 qt. casserole, place raw meat, sprinkle with salt, add onion, celery, and carrots.
Sprinkle with sugar and tapioca. Pour V8 juice over all.
Cover tightly with foil
if casserole dish does not have a lid.
Bake 4 hours at 250 degrees.
You may also cube 3 or 4 small potatoes and put in with the vegetables.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil until golden brown. Add onion and garlic.
In a small bowl, combine all other ingredients except mushrooms, pepper and tomatoes.
Pour this over the chicken. Stir occasionally and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add fresh vegetables and cover.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes more. Serve immediately with rice, pasta or bread.
Also tastes great! (Be sure to remove bay leaf after cooking.)

title: chicken & wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into baking dish. Bake for 25-30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Note: Makes 2 dozen cookies. Can substitute chopped dates or raisins for the chocolate chips in these cookies.

title: quick tomato slaw
directions: Combine salad dressing and mustard.
Place remaining ingredients in salad bowl.
Add dressing.
Toss carefully until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix together lime jello, hot water, 1/2 cup drained pineapple juice, cream cheese, sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Add 7-Up last. Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm; unmold and serve. Garnish as desired.

title: iced brownies
directions: Cream the first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic over medium heat with oil in Dutch oven until soft.
Stir in zucchini, squash, bell pepper, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 8 minutes.
Stir often until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Cover. Reduce heat to low and let simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Add enough water to cook soft. blend in blender until smooth.
Add all ingredients and cook at least 2 hours on slow burner.
Stir frequently to prevent burning. Pour into sterilized jars to within half inch of top.
Put on caps and screw band tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: pecan toffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add 2 cups sugar and stir until golden brown. Add pecans and pour out on cookie sheet.
Stretch it thin.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in oil or bacon fat.
Peel and cut eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat in small amount of water in covered pan about 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Drain.
Add tomatoes.
Add bread cubes until some juice is taken up.
Add onions and peppers.
Mix in cheese cubes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Put into casserole dish.
Add Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease three 8-inch cake pans. Line bottoms with wax paper. Grease and flour paper. Heat milk and coffee in small saucepan until small bubbles form around edge. Add to cocoa and whisk until smooth. Whisk in sour cream. Cool. In a medium bowl. combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Beat butter in mixer bowl until light. Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. At low speed, gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with chocolate mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 25 minutes, until top springs back when lightly touched. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Invert cakes onto rack. Remove paper and cool complete, right side up.

title: corn pudding
directions: Scald milk and add butter to melt.
Put corn in large mixing bowl and add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add eggs and again mix. Slowly pour in milk.
Stir to mix.
Bake in 2-quart shallow baking dish (that has been well greased) for 35 minutes or in a deeper dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb squares
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cinnamon and chopped nuts together, then set aside.
That's the topping.
Mix rest of ingredients together; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then add topping.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° (325° if glass dish).

title: ham loaves
directions: In a bowl, combine pork, ham, crumbs, eggs and milk.
Shape into 12 ovals, using 1 cup of mixture for each.
Place in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, water, vinegar and mustard; pour over loaves.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting every 15 to 20 minutes. Place the loaves on a platter and spoon some of the sauce over them.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: heshwi
directions: Brown beef and onions in butter; do not drain.
Add spices (can adjust to taste).
Add rice and brown for a few minutes, mixing well.
Add chicken broth, water or combination of both (2 to 2 1/4 cups per cup rice).
Bring to a boil and cook over very low heat until rice is done, stirring once or twice.
Serve with tomato and cucumber salad and plain yogurt.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk and curry powder and warm on top of stove.
Put chicken, broccoli and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over this and top with French onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Note:
Bridgeford bread is frozen dough.
Thaw loaf in fridge the night before you plan to make Sausage Bread.

title: chili beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce in heavy skillet. Cook until meat loses its pink color and onion becomes transparent. Add tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes to an hour.
Put with one can pintos and 1 can kidney beans.
Brown meat and add other ingredients and simmer on low all day in crock-pot.

title: linguine and vegetables
directions: Cook linguine.
