When cooled add vegetables, dressing and seasoning.
Mix and refrigerate.
Can add any variety of vegetables.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: *Pecans may be substituted instead of peanuts.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; spill onto flat cookie sheet (jelly roll pan).
Press evenly around.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until light brown.
Let cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, Cool Whip or Dream Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled crust.
Top with canned pie filling or fresh fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: pear jelly
directions: You will need sterilized jars.

title: triple-cheese manicotti
directions: Combine water, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix in a small saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Mix 1 cup Mozzarella, Ricotta, Parmesan, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stuff cheese mixture into cooked shells, using about 1/4 cup for each shell.

title: quick as a wink chili rellenos
directions: If using fresh peppers, after peeling and seeding, cook in microwave on high for 2 minutes with 1 Tbsp. water in a covered pyrex dish.
(To be sure they are well done for main dish.)

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together thoroughly and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into sheet cake pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in the sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped Cool Whip; blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Garnish with fresh sliced strawberries, or use cherry pie mixture.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add oil, garlic, parsley flakes, basil or Italian seasoning, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook noodles and a little salt.
Add oil to water so noodles won't stick.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 2 tablespoons parsley flakes.
Layer in pan the noodles, cheese mixture, meat sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese on top melts.

title: aunt zee's pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Top with strips of pastry.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and bake until bubbly and brown on top.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stuff in pita pockets.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Chop all vegetables you use.
Press crescent rolls onto a large cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°; cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing, then spread over crust.
Place veggies on top, then shredded carrots and grated cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add beaten eggs and beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in 9-inch pie pan with unbaked shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven.
Melt margarine and blend everything in blender; add coconut last, and blend a minute or two.
Pour into pie crust (Pet-Ritz small pie shells, not deep dish) and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Before putting pies in oven, sprinkle a bit of coconut on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown together ground beef and onion in a large pot.
Season meat with seasoning salt, then add (including juice) kidney beans, pinto beans, stewed tomatoes, hominy, tomato juice and diced green chilies.
Stir and add taco seasoning and Ranch dressing (optional).
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
This can either be served with crackers or is delicious served over corn chips.
This is great for serving the multitudes.
This may also be frozen.

title: sweet & sour meatballs
directions: Mix sweet & sour sauce and bell peppers together in slow cooker.
Pour thawed meatballs in slow cooker.
Stir to coat meatballs with sauce and simmer on low heat for about 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hot-n-honey chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips; cut each wing into 1/2 at joint.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine 3/4 cup picante sauce, honey, soy sauce, mustard, oil, ginger and orange peel in small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken wings.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Preheat oven at 400°.
Place chicken and sauce in single layer on foil-lined 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with additional picante sauce. Makes about 45.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Peel and shred zucchini.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix again.
Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer onion in butter until tender.
Stir in chopped broccoli.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into deep casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: deanne's pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip to above mixture and blend.
Add the marshmallows and chopped pecans to the whole mixture.
Spread in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish or bowl and chill.

title: ruth's supper rolls
directions: Place shortening and sugar in bowl.
Add water; stir well. Stir in yeast.
Add flour all at once; beat with fork to make soft dough.
Cover; let rise for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or place in refrigerator until ready to let rise.
Knead down; make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Boil together sugar, vinegar, water and mustard seed; let cool. Mix together cabbage, celery, carrots and diced peppers.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture.
Salt to taste.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: You can buy yogurt culture or simply use an unflavored yogurt that has a live culture (such as Dannon) as your starter. Sterilize all the equipment with boiling water just before you start.
Heat the milk to scalding and then cool it down to 110°. Put the milk into small jars or cups. Add 1 tablespoon yogurt to each pint.
Incubate at 110° for 3 to 6 hours or overnight.
A commercial yogurt maker will hold the temperature.
You can put your jars of yogurt on a heating pad (warm setting) and cover them with towels.
You can also sit them in the oven right above the pilot light.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Shake chicken in Baggie with cornflakes and cheese.
Melt margarine.
Spoon on top of chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Measure and then put oatmeal in the blender.
Blend to a fine powder.
Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Mix in flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add grated candy bars, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with the first 2 ingredients.
Mix chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar until smooth, then drop by tablespoon on top of cake batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
When cake is done, it will look "cracked" like an earthquake.
Invert pieces to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Drain part of juice; then mix dry instant jello over it and stir.
It will soon set and the jello keeps the bananas from turning dark.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese enough to work in
all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pepper and 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Beat 1 egg, ice water and vinegar.
Add to dry ingredients.
Makes 2 bottoms and 2 tops of pie.

title: sea foam candy
directions: Mix brown sugar, water and cream of tartar in sauce pan. Cook with lid on until sugar crystals melt.
Continue cooking on medium heat until it thickens slightly.
Start testing by pouring small portion from spoon and continue until a hair-like portion flies out.
Should be 4 to 5 inches.
Pour immediately over egg whites in mixer.
Continue beating until it loses it's shiny appearance. Spoon out on slightly buttered sheet of wax paper.

title: spicy sugar nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Place nuts in a small bowl.
Pour egg whites over nuts and stir until nuts are coated and sticky. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over nuts, stirring until sugar mixture completely coats nuts.
Spread nuts on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields approximately 2 cups.

title: crisp toffee bars
directions: Thoroughly cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Press mixture into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) 25 minutes or until browned.
While warm, cut in bars or squares.
Cool before removing from pan. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except oats, flour and raisins.
Stir in oats, flour and raisins.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: chippers
directions: Mix together like pastry.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until light brown, 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pakoray
directions: Sift the gram flour into a large bowl.
Add the spices, baking powder, cumin and pomegranate seed.
Blend.
Add water and beat well to form a smooth batter.
Add coriander and leave aside.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and stir in brown sugar.
Let sugar mixture cool and beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour mixture and chocolate bits.
Pour into greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool, then cut in squares.

title: strawberry-rhubarb angel squares
directions: Cook rhubarb in water for 10 minutes till come to boil.
Stir in jello and cook two more minutes.
Stir often.
Add berries till they break apart.
Refrigerate two - three hours till thickens. Then layer 1/2 mixture, cool whip and cake.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Separately combine milk and pudding.
Stir Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Add cream cheese mixture to pudding mixture a little at a time.
Sprinkle a layer of crushed Oreo cookies on the bottom of an 8-inch platter lined with tinfoil.
Spoon a layer of pudding mixture on top of that.
Sprinkle with Oreo cookies.
Repeat process.
Save some of the crushed Oreos for the top layer.

title: bagels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and sugar.
Let yeast work for about 15 minutes.
Add this to other dry ingredients.
Mix and remove from bowl.
Knead on floured surface for about 12 minutes, adding flour as needed to keep dough from being sticky.
Set aside in a bowl covered with cloth until doubled in size (1 to 2 hours).

title: easy christmas fudge
directions: Pour condensed milk into nonstick pan; heat until milk begins to bubble.
Pour in chocolate chips and stir.
Also add vanilla while stirring.
Remove from heat immediately and fold in pecans. Pour candy into square cake pan that has first been sprayed with Pam.
Put into freezer until hardened.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, salt, cream of tartar and cook on medium-high until it forms a soft ball. Stir to avoid sticking. Take off heat and add butter, vanilla and peanut butter if desired. Beat until the shine is gone or until reasonable thickness. Pour on greased waxed paper in a square pan and cut into square when cool.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Don't make too stiff.
Allow to roll off spoon without having to shake.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika
and
pepper.	Add
salad oil. Dip chicken in mixture coating well.
Bake in a shallow pan at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.	Makes 6 servings.

title: spiral apple tart
directions: Stir flour and sugar in a bowl.
Cut the butter in the flour until butter pieces are pea size.
Press into 11-inch tart pan. Cover with plastic wrap and place in freezer while filling is prepared.

title: green chili stew
directions: Saute onions while cutting meat into small pieces.
Brown meat and onions in a little oil, just until meat is grayish.
Put all ingredients in big pot with onion and meat.
Cover and simmer 5 to 6 hours.
Stir often.
Great with flour tortillas.

title: president ronald reagan's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender and drain.
Stir in butter and egg. Mix mustard, salt and water.
Add milk.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over macaroni.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until top is crusty.

title: biscuit dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add butter and mix well.
Add buttermilk to mix.
Knead dough on floured surface.
Roll out 3/4-inch thick and 2-inches round.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 450°.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool and add 7-Up, marshmallows, pineapple and bananas.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Cook until thickened the pineapple juice, sugar, egg, flour and cream cheese.
Remove from heat and add oleo.
Cool.
Add whipped topping.
Put over jello and top with coconut.

title: wiener blankets
directions: Split wiener end to end, one side fill with cheese spread. Separate crescent roll into triangles; place wiener on each triangle and roll as directed on label.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: orletta's chile egg puff
directions: Blend eggs with mixer until light and lemon colored. Add remaining ingredients, except chilies. Stir in chilies. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In saucepan melt milk, chips and oleo.
Just melt (do not boil).
Pour over marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into buttered dish. Let stand or chill 2 hours.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle on top. Chill till cold or overnight.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; reserve 2/3 cup for top of pie. Press rest into pie pan for crust.
Cook remaining ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Add egg whites of 3 beaten eggs to cool custard.
Put in pie crust and cover with remaining topping crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Blend sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Then add nuts and vanilla. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: sour cream corn bread(8 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients, just enough to blend well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pan (square).
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Cook until thick enough for pies, stirring frequently.
Can in sterile jars while hot and process.

title: banana bread
directions: Use processor or electric mixer and beat well the bananas and vegetable oil.
Add to rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased loaf pan (5 x 9-inch.)
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: marble cake
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake comes out dry when tested by straw.
Mix butter, margarine, sugar and egg yolks together until smooth.
Sift cake flour and baking powder together and alternate milk and flour.
Beat egg whites until firm and fold into batter.
Measure chocolate syrup and then take half of batter and pour in syrup.
Then put white batter and chocolate, alternating until finished.
Take spatula and mix to form marble. Bake in 10-inch angel like form.
Butter form.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for one minute.
Place in raw pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake like a custard pie, about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clear 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with a large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Separately sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add to mixture.
Next add milk slowly, mixing well.
Add flavoring.
Cook for 1 hour at 375° or 400°.
Check with toothpick.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 in. dish.

title: swiss steak
directions: Make beef into patties and fry until brown.
Put browned patties into an oven dish.
Pour can of tomatoes, diced peppers and seasonings over patties.
Simmer approximately 30 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Pour into a 10-inch Bundt pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until cake tests done. Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice until of spreading consistency and ice cake.

title: christmas cranberry mold
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until soft.
Add gelatin and cool.
Refrigerate until it starts to set.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour in mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: goulash
directions: In a large pan, brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and bell pepper (diced).
Then add the Ro-Tel tomatoes,
tomato sauce and water.
Cook the macaroni in a separate pan until it is soft; drain the water off and add the goulash.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Separate the cream filling from the wafers of the cookies. Put each in separate bowls.
Add remaining ingredients to the cream of the cookies and mix well.
Crush the cookies until they are to a dirt-looking state.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil in saucepan.
Stir in dry Jell-O and mix until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill again until partially set.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Chop onions; add to meat.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Chop the tomatoes and add them and juice to meat.
Add remaining seasonings.
Add seasonings to suit your taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed. Put small amount of meat sauce on bottom of large baking dish. Layer noodles, meat, cottage cheese, Parmesan, Mozzarella, noodles, meat, etc.
End with Parmesan cheese.
Make 3 layers.

title: shortcake
directions: Sift 2 cups flour with other dry ingredients. Cut in butter and shortening. Mix in buttermilk. Add remaining 1/2-cup flour if mixture seems too wet. Knead 10 times. Pat out on a floured board about 1-inch thick. Cut into four pieces and shape in circles. Place apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle tops with sugar. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool on pan. Split each cake and lightly spread each with butter. Top with strawberry filling and whipped cream.

title: glazed leg of lamb
directions: Sprinkle lamb with salt and pepper.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Roast in oven preheated to 325° for 20 to 25 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer registers 145° for medium-rare doneness.

title: oyster roll
directions: Cream the mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion and salt.
Spread 1/2 inch thick on wax paper into a 6 x 8-inch rectangle.
Put oysters on top and roll.
Chill cream cheese mixture first before rolling; it will be easier. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: gallipolis emblem club potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with peelings.
Cool, skin and dice.
Melt butter and saute onions and peppers.
Add soups and milk.
Fold in cheese until melted.
Add pimentos.
Pour over potatoes and cook at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 75 people.

title: ableskievers(danish)
directions: Stir all ingredients together.	Add soda to milk before stirring.
Then
beat
the	egg
whites and fold into mixture. These
take
a
special pan but bake as pancakes if pan is not available.	Serve with syrup, jello, brown sugar, etc.

title: garlic meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, using a food processor.
Form into small balls.
Fry or boil on greased surface for 10 to 15 minutes, turning every so often.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage and drain well.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, line casserole with cubed bread squares; sprinkle sausage over bread, then grated cheese over sausage.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate, covered (foil will do), overnight.
The next morning, bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Casserole will be firm when cooked.
Cut into squares.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form, about 5-8 minutes.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 200° for 50 to 55 minutes or until firm.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: banana sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the oleo and water.
Add to all the remaining ingredients, mix well.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together
and
pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: holiday coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir butter, eggs and salt into yeast mixture.
Stir in flour.
Beat flour mixture at medium speed until a crumbly dough forms.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, 5 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in a large greased bowl, turning to coat.
Cover loosely with a damp cloth and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza(as a main dish)
directions: Lay flat rolls in ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Blend together mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread mixture over cooled rolls.
Add dry, fresh vegetables.
Do not cover tightly.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Blend cookies in blender, real fine cookie crumbs.
Mix cookie crumbs and butter together.
Press this in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream, spread this over the cookie layer and freeze.
Spread chocolate over the ice cream and freeze.
Spread Cool Whip on top and freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice
in greased casserole dish.
Put in half of broth to moisten rice.
Cover with chicken.
Spread on mixture of soups, sour cream
and rest of broth on top.
Cover with sliced mushrooms.	Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.	Remove dish, top with cheese, and return to oven for about 5 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir until thick. Add butter, salt, vanilla and chocolate square.
Serve warm.

title: banana chutney
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a saucepan and simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Pour the mixture into sterilized jars and store in the refrigerator.
Serve as a side dish with any curry or as a garnish with cold beef, chicken or ham.
No sugar added.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar and put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except orange juice and milk.
Mix well (takes a very large container to mix in).
Add orange juice and milk and pack firmly into a wax paper lined pan.
(Use loaf or round tin.)
Cover with foil or lid and refrigerate for at least 2 days before serving.

title: creamed cheesecake
directions: Mix cake mix, 3 eggs and margarine.
Pour evenly into pan. Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour evenly on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cup sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough by rounding teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Roll balls into mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: polish chop suey cake
directions: Mix all by hand; do not beat.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
When cool frost with:

title: three-in-one refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in potatoes, sugar, shortening, salt, eggs and 5 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a firm dough. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 7 minutes. Place in a large greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Punch dough down. Turn onto a lightly floured surface. Divide dough into 3 portions. Make into cloverleaf or pan rolls. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled. Bake at 400° for 16 minutes. Brush with melted butter.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti.
Place sauce in bottom of oblong casserole dish. Then layer ziti, meat, cheese and sauce.
Then make another layer of the same.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-up
directions: Mix cheese, cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add chilies and olives; mix well.
Spread on tortillas to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Roll up, starting at one edge.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate about 6 hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices and serve with picante sauce.

title: veg beef soup
directions: Drain most of juice from tomatoes and empty into a 2 gallon pot.
Add corn, peas, green beans and carrots.
Add chopped onions and potatoes.
Add broth or bouillon.
Cut up the 3 packages of dried beef and add some of the tomato juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Adjust heat to a slow steady simmer, stirring often to keep from burning.
As mixture cooks down, keep adding tomato juice.
Cook for approximately 2 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Boil for ten to twenty minutes. Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and plain jello; mix well.
Seal in jelly jars.
May also be used for pie filling.
Freezes well.

title: stuffed artichoke
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put bread crumbs in each leaf. Then put artichokes in a pot of boiling water.
Put oil over them and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and orange peel.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well with creamed mixture.
Add milk; beat well.
Fold in raisins, nuts and poppy seed.
Spoon into greased muffin tins about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mama's ice cream custard
directions: Beat
eggs
well.
Add	sugar
and flour that have been mixed together.
Add
quarts of whole milk or 5 cans evaporated milk plus
water to make a total of 3 quarts.
Add salt and cook
over low
heat
until
it thickens or coats a metal spoon.
Cool
in cold
water
and
freeze.
May add any fruit (peaches, strawberries,
etc.) but always sweeten fresh fruit and add
the juice
of
one lemon.
Can use canned pineapple, drained with no extra sugar.

title: hot chicken-chip salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and pour into a baking dish. Sprinkle with the cheese and chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until no longer pink. Cook spaghetti as directed and drain. Saute onion in butter and set aside. Cut chicken into strips or cubes and add to spaghetti. Add onion and chicken broth. Put on low heat and add remaining ingredients. Simmer until cheese is melted. Makes a very large pot. Tastes better the second day.

title: hamburger maki pupu
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the nori.
Roll the mixture in nori like sushi,
in
5/8-inch diameter.
Wrap each roll in wax paper.
Freeze
overnight.	Slice
each
roll
in 4 pieces while frozen.
Deep fry.	You can keep in freezer indefinitely and cook as needed for pupus or side dish.

title: chicken simplicity
directions: Mix mushroom soup with chicken soup or water.
Place fryer in baking dish.
Pour rice over chicken.
Sprinkle dry soup over rice.
Then pour liquid soups over this.
Bake at 435° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pineapple on the grill
directions: Place each pineapple slice on an 8-inch square of heavy-duty foil.
Fill centers with 1 tablespoon preserves and coconut; fold into tight package.
Heat on a preheated grill at low position for 10 minutes or until preserves have melted over pineapple.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked ziti
directions: Brown sausage, onions, garlic, mushrooms and eggplant.
Saute until vegetables are tender; drain off fat.
Add salt and pepper. Set aside.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture, skin side up; drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt, paprika and poultry seasoning.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with vegetables.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine sugar, allspice, cloves, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cider in a large saucepan.
Slowly bring to a boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove whole spices.
Serve in warmed mugs with a clove studded orange wedge in each.

title: sorrel soup
directions: Fry an onion in olive oil until translucent.
Add sorrel leaves and let melt until it forms a thick sauce.
Heat broth in pot. Add potatoes; cook until they start to fall apart.
Add the sorrel sauce. Whisk all until smooth. Serve with a dollop of sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine flour, nuts and melted oleo.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well; then fold Cool Whip in.
Spread over cool crust; then spread cherry pie filling over top.
Chill several hours.

title: louisburg cafe bread pudding
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend in pieces of bread, rolls or doughnuts.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Makes 24 servings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar, eggs and dates in an iron skillet about 20 minutes or long enough to cook eggs.
Add vanilla, nuts and cereal.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll balls in coconut or ground pecans.

title: spinach loaf
directions: In a large bowl, knead together (like making pie crust dough) all ingredients except the spinach.
Mix quickly.
When well mixed, add spinach and knead well.
Butter loaf pan or use foil and pat the mixture into it.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
The loaf is done when the crust forms on the surface. For a light meal, add one cup of diced ham and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt together.
Cut up fresh strawberries and add to the mixture.
Line a bowl with plain ladyfinger cakes. Spoon in mixture around lining.
Add another row of ladyfinger cakes and spoon in more mixture.
Place fresh strawberries around the top to make a pretty pattern.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Blend the ingredients
together
in
a
heavy saucepan. Bring to
a boil and boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and beat for 30 seconds or until foamy.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until moist.
Stir in beaten egg white last.

title: peppermints
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets.
In a saucepan, combine the brown sugar, vinegar, water and syrup.
Cook until the mixture forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Then add peppermint oil. Mix well.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese until soft and add frosting and Cool Whip.
Add 3 tablespoons of lemon juice to mix.
Place in crust.
Garnish with favorite fruits or nuts.

title: extra special biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening, using a pastry blender or two knives.
Add the milk and stir until mixture forms a ball.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface and knead gently about 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick; cut into rounds.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 10 (2 1/2-inch) biscuits.

title: rice pudding
directions: Lightly beat egg and egg white together.
Mix rice with skim milk, egg, raisins, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick (about 5 minutes after milk boils).
Makes 4 servings.

title: garlic chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken lightly over low heat in butter with garlic, onion and carrot.
Place chicken and vegetables in baking dish. Combine sherry, parsley, salt, basil and pepper with pan juices. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting several times.
Add water, if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yellow rice
directions: Brown the chicken pieces in combination of olive oil (3/4 of small bottle) and Wesson oil (approximately 1 cup). In large turkey roaster pan, place the rice, food coloring, salt, dried onion flakes, garlic powder and tomato juice or tomatoes (rinse can or jar and add to mix). Place chicken on top of rice mixture and pour leftover oils over all. Press with a spoon to allow oils to penetrate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Divide mix in half.
To half of mix, add 1 cup melted butter and 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk and blend.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While 1st layer is baking, melt Kraft caramels with 1 cup butter and other half can Eagle Brand milk. Add nuts.
Pour this mixture over baked layer.
Pour remaining German chocolate cake mix over caramel mixture and bake another 20 to 25 minutes.
Place Hershey bars on top of hot cake and spread as they melt.
Very rich!

title: chicken andabya
directions: Combine orange juice, garlic flakes and parsley for marinade. Marinate chicken overnight or for a few hours.
Dip chicken in seasoned flour; fry until brown (do not overcook).
Remove chicken and pour oil out of pan.
Add butter and sherry and heat until glazed.
Add raisins and olives.
Bake chicken at 375° about 25 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken last 5 minutes.

title: new year's eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Pour this mixture in 4 glasses.
Fill only 2/3 high, then drop a tablespoon of strawberry ice cream into each glass.
Serve cold.
Serves 4.

title: baked crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cracker meal and butter; place in casserole.
Combine cracker meal and butter and sprinkle over salad.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake. Serve hot.

title: cheese pepper bread
directions: Grease two 1 pound coffee cans.
In a large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add 1 1/3 cups flour, sugar, salt, soda, sour cream and egg.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 2 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in remaining flour, cheese and pepper thoroughly.
Divide batter between cans.
Let rise in warm place 50 minutes.
(Batter will rise slightly but will not double.) Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from cans.
Cool slightly before slicing. Makes 2 loaves.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Combine with hand mixer.
Add shrimp last.
Serve at room temperature with Wheat Thins or Triscuits.
Good to have on hand in the freezer.
Divide into 2 or 3 small containers and freeze.

title: peanut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening over hot, not boiling, water.
Remove from hot water.
With wooden spoon, beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Sift flour with baking powder into chocolate mixture; stir to mix well.
Stir in peanuts.
Turn mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes. Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple crisp
directions: Put the pineapple in a casserole dish.
Mix the sugar, flour and reserved juice.
Pour over the pineapple.
Top with the cheese.
Mix the cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Spread on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot and zucchini salad
directions: Shred the carrots on the coarse side of a grater or use the coarse grating blade of a food processor.
Place in a large bowl. Grate the zucchini in the same way and add to the carrots.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and powdered milk. Add all other ingredients. Mix well. Knead for at least 10 minutes. Put back in greased bowl and let rise until double, punch down and let rise again.

title: apple whole wheat waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Put other ingredients in blender, blend just until apple is pureed.
Add to flour mix.
Bake in preheated waffle iron.
Makes 8.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In saucepan, cook Minute rice.
Set aside.
In small skillet, saute egg noodles in butter until golden (now is the time to saute onions or pepper too).
Mix with rice.
Serve hot.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in juice, garlic and seasonings 15 minutes. Cook chicken in oil 2 to 3 minutes until it loses pink color.
Add onions and peppers.
Continue cooking 3 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in salsa.
Spoon over tortillas.
Top with cheese.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Melt
butter,
cool.
Beat
eggs; add sugar and butter, stir. Add all other ingredients.	Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry shortcake
directions: Cream the butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add the egg, flour and baking powder.
Put the raspberries in a 9-inch plate and sprinkle with the 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread batter over the berries.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
May substitute the raspberries for strawberries, if desired.

title: holiday punch
directions: Follow	directions
on Kool-Aid package.
Add pineapple juice. Freeze this
mixture until mushy.	Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
If you want to make green instead of red, use lemon/lime Kool-Aid.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown meat.
Mix with remaining ingredients except noodles. Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add noodles and bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
